45 void RISCVDAGToDAGISel::PreprocessISelDAG() { 0
46 SelectionDAG::allnodes_iterator Position = CurDAG->allnodes_end(); 0
47 ----
48 bool MadeChange = false; 0
49 while (Position != CurDAG->allnodes_begin()) { 0
50 SDNode *N = &*--Position; 0
51 if (N->use_empty()) 0
52 continue; 0
53 ----
54 SDValue Result; 0
55 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
56 case ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR: { 0
57 // Convert integer SPLAT_VECTOR to VMV_V_X_VL and floating-point ----
58 // SPLAT_VECTOR to VFMV_V_F_VL to reduce isel burden. ----
59 MVT VT = N->getSimpleValueType(0); 0
60 unsigned Opc = ----
61 VT.isInteger() ? RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL : RISCVISD::VFMV_V_F_VL; 0
62 SDLoc DL(N); 0
63 SDValue VL = CurDAG->getRegister(RISCV::X0, Subtarget->getXLenVT()); 0
64 Result = CurDAG->getNode(Opc, DL, VT, CurDAG->getUNDEF(VT), 0
65 N->getOperand(0), VL); 0
66 break; 0
67 } 0
68 case RISCVISD::SPLAT_VECTOR_SPLIT_I64_VL: { 0
69 // Lower SPLAT_VECTOR_SPLIT_I64 to two scalar stores and a stride 0 vector ----
70 // load. Done after lowering and combining so that we have a chance to ----
71 // optimize this to VMV_V_X_VL when the upper bits aren't needed. ----
72 assert(N->getNumOperands() == 4 && "Unexpected number of operands"); 0
73 MVT VT = N->getSimpleValueType(0); 0
74 SDValue Passthru = N->getOperand(0); 0
75 SDValue Lo = N->getOperand(1); 0
76 SDValue Hi = N->getOperand(2); 0
77 SDValue VL = N->getOperand(3); 0
78 assert(VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i64 && VT.isScalableVector() && 0
79 Lo.getValueType() == MVT::i32 && Hi.getValueType() == MVT::i32 && ----
80 "Unexpected VTs!"); ----
81 MachineFunction &MF = CurDAG->getMachineFunction(); 0
82 SDLoc DL(N); 0
83 ----
84 // Create temporary stack for each expanding node. ----
85 SDValue StackSlot = ----
86 CurDAG->CreateStackTemporary(TypeSize::Fixed(8), Align(4)); 0
87 int FI = cast(StackSlot.getNode())->getIndex(); 0
88 MachinePointerInfo MPI = MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI); 0
89 ----
90 SDValue Chain = CurDAG->getEntryNode(); 0
91 Lo = CurDAG->getStore(Chain, DL, Lo, StackSlot, MPI, Align(8)); 0
92 ----
93 SDValue OffsetSlot = ----
94 CurDAG->getMemBasePlusOffset(StackSlot, TypeSize::Fixed(4), DL); 0
95 Hi = CurDAG->getStore(Chain, DL, Hi, OffsetSlot, MPI.getWithOffset(4), 0
96 Align(8)); ----
97 ----
98 Chain = CurDAG->getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, DL, MVT::Other, Lo, Hi); 0
99 ----
100 SDVTList VTs = CurDAG->getVTList({VT, MVT::Other}); 0
101 SDValue IntID = ----
102 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Intrinsic::riscv_vlse, DL, MVT::i64); 0
103 SDValue Ops[] = {Chain, ----
104 IntID, ----
105 Passthru, ----
106 StackSlot, ----
107 CurDAG->getRegister(RISCV::X0, MVT::i64), 0
108 VL}; 0
109 ----
110 Result = CurDAG->getMemIntrinsicNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN, DL, VTs, Ops, 0
111 MVT::i64, MPI, Align(8), ----
112 MachineMemOperand::MOLoad); ----
113 break; 0
114 } 0
115 } ----
116 ----
117 if (Result) { 0
118 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "RISC-V DAG preprocessing replacing:\nOld: "); 0
119 LLVM_DEBUG(N->dump(CurDAG)); 0
120 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\nNew: "); 0
121 LLVM_DEBUG(Result->dump(CurDAG)); 0
122 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\n"); 0
123 ----
124 CurDAG->ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(N, 0), Result); 0
125 MadeChange = true; 0
126 } ----
127 } ----
128 ----
129 if (MadeChange) 0
130 CurDAG->RemoveDeadNodes(); 0
131 } 0

133 void RISCVDAGToDAGISel::PostprocessISelDAG() { 0
134 HandleSDNode Dummy(CurDAG->getRoot()); 0
135 SelectionDAG::allnodes_iterator Position = CurDAG->allnodes_end(); 0
136 ----
137 bool MadeChange = false; 0
138 while (Position != CurDAG->allnodes_begin()) { 0
139 SDNode *N = &*--Position; 0
140 // Skip dead nodes and any non-machine opcodes. ----
141 if (N->use_empty() || !N->isMachineOpcode()) 0
142 continue; 0
143 ----
144 MadeChange |= doPeepholeSExtW(N); 0
145 MadeChange |= doPeepholeMaskedRVV(N); 0
146 } ----
147 ----
148 CurDAG->setRoot(Dummy.getValue()); 0
149 ----
150 MadeChange |= doPeepholeMergeVVMFold(); 0
151 ----
152 if (MadeChange) 0
153 CurDAG->RemoveDeadNodes(); 0
154 } 0

156 static SDValue selectImmSeq(SelectionDAG *CurDAG, const SDLoc &DL, const MVT VT, 0
157 RISCVMatInt::InstSeq &Seq) { ----
158 SDValue SrcReg = CurDAG->getRegister(RISCV::X0, VT); 0
159 for (const RISCVMatInt::Inst &Inst : Seq) { 0
160 SDValue SDImm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Inst.getImm(), DL, VT); 0
161 SDNode *Result = nullptr; 0
162 switch (Inst.getOpndKind()) { 0
163 case RISCVMatInt::Imm: 0
164 Result = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Inst.getOpcode(), DL, VT, SDImm); 0
165 break; 0
166 case RISCVMatInt::RegX0: 0
167 Result = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Inst.getOpcode(), DL, VT, SrcReg, 0
168 CurDAG->getRegister(RISCV::X0, VT)); ----
169 break; 0
170 case RISCVMatInt::RegReg: 0
171 Result = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Inst.getOpcode(), DL, VT, SrcReg, SrcReg); 0
172 break; 0
173 case RISCVMatInt::RegImm: 0
174 Result = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Inst.getOpcode(), DL, VT, SrcReg, SDImm); 0
175 break; 0
176 } ----
177 ----
178 // Only the first instruction has X0 as its source. ----
179 SrcReg = SDValue(Result, 0); 0
180 } ----
181 ----
182 return SrcReg; 0
183 } ----
184 ----
185 static SDValue selectImm(SelectionDAG *CurDAG, const SDLoc &DL, const MVT VT, 0
186 int64_t Imm, const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget) { ----
187 RISCVMatInt::InstSeq Seq = ----
188 RISCVMatInt::generateInstSeq(Imm, Subtarget.getFeatureBits()); 0
189 ----
190 // See if we can create this constant as (ADD (SLLI X, 32), X) where X is at ----
191 // worst an LUI+ADDIW. This will require an extra register, but avoids a ----
192 // constant pool. ----
193 if (Seq.size() > 3) { 0
194 int64_t LoVal = SignExtend64<32>(Imm); 0
195 int64_t HiVal = SignExtend64<32>(((uint64_t)Imm - (uint64_t)LoVal) >> 32); 0
196 if (LoVal == HiVal) { 0
197 RISCVMatInt::InstSeq SeqLo = ----
198 RISCVMatInt::generateInstSeq(LoVal, Subtarget.getFeatureBits()); 0
199 if ((SeqLo.size() + 2) < Seq.size()) { 0
200 SDValue Lo = selectImmSeq(CurDAG, DL, VT, SeqLo); 0
201 ----
202 SDValue SLLI = SDValue( ----
203 CurDAG->getMachineNode(RISCV::SLLI, DL, VT, Lo, 0
204 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(32, DL, VT)), ----
205 0); 0
206 return SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode(RISCV::ADD, DL, VT, Lo, SLLI), 0
207 0); 0
208 } ----
209 } 0
210 } ----
211 ----
212 // Otherwise, use the original sequence. ----
213 return selectImmSeq(CurDAG, DL, VT, Seq); 0
214 } 0

216 static SDValue createTuple(SelectionDAG &CurDAG, ArrayRef Regs, 0
217 unsigned NF, RISCVII::VLMUL LMUL) { ----
218 static const unsigned M1TupleRegClassIDs[] = { ----
219 RISCV::VRN2M1RegClassID, RISCV::VRN3M1RegClassID, RISCV::VRN4M1RegClassID, ----
220 RISCV::VRN5M1RegClassID, RISCV::VRN6M1RegClassID, RISCV::VRN7M1RegClassID, ----
221 RISCV::VRN8M1RegClassID}; ----
222 static const unsigned M2TupleRegClassIDs[] = {RISCV::VRN2M2RegClassID, ----
223 RISCV::VRN3M2RegClassID, ----
224 RISCV::VRN4M2RegClassID}; ----
225 ----
226 assert(Regs.size() >= 2 && Regs.size() <= 8); 0
227 ----
228 unsigned RegClassID; ----
229 unsigned SubReg0; ----
230 switch (LMUL) { 0
231 default: 0
232 llvm_unreachable("Invalid LMUL."); 0
233 case RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_F8: 0
234 case RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_F4: ----
235 case RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_F2: ----
236 case RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_1: ----
237 static_assert(RISCV::sub_vrm1_7 == RISCV::sub_vrm1_0 + 7, ----
238 "Unexpected subreg numbering"); ----
239 SubReg0 = RISCV::sub_vrm1_0; 0
240 RegClassID = M1TupleRegClassIDs[NF - 2]; 0
241 break; 0
242 case RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_2: 0
243 static_assert(RISCV::sub_vrm2_3 == RISCV::sub_vrm2_0 + 3, ----
244 "Unexpected subreg numbering"); ----
245 SubReg0 = RISCV::sub_vrm2_0; 0
246 RegClassID = M2TupleRegClassIDs[NF - 2]; 0
247 break; 0
248 case RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_4: 0
249 static_assert(RISCV::sub_vrm4_1 == RISCV::sub_vrm4_0 + 1, ----
250 "Unexpected subreg numbering"); ----
251 SubReg0 = RISCV::sub_vrm4_0; 0
252 RegClassID = RISCV::VRN2M4RegClassID; 0
253 break; 0
254 } ----
255 ----
256 SDLoc DL(Regs[0]); 0
257 SmallVector Ops; 0
258 ----
259 Ops.push_back(CurDAG.getTargetConstant(RegClassID, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
260 ----
261 for (unsigned I = 0; I < Regs.size(); ++I) { 0
262 Ops.push_back(Regs[I]); 0
263 Ops.push_back(CurDAG.getTargetConstant(SubReg0 + I, DL, MVT::i32)); 0
264 } ----
265 SDNode *N = ----
266 CurDAG.getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE, DL, MVT::Untyped, Ops); 0
267 return SDValue(N, 0); 0
268 } ----

270 void RISCVDAGToDAGISel::addVectorLoadStoreOperands( 0
271 SDNode *Node, unsigned Log2SEW, const SDLoc &DL, unsigned CurOp, ----
272 bool IsMasked, bool IsStridedOrIndexed, SmallVectorImpl &Operands, ----
273 bool IsLoad, MVT *IndexVT) { ----
274 SDValue Chain = Node->getOperand(0); 0
275 SDValue Glue; 0
276 ----
277 Operands.push_back(Node->getOperand(CurOp++)); // Base pointer. 0
278 ----
279 if (IsStridedOrIndexed) { 0
280 Operands.push_back(Node->getOperand(CurOp++)); // Index. 0
281 if (IndexVT) 0
282 *IndexVT = Operands.back()->getSimpleValueType(0); 0
283 } ----
284 ----
285 if (IsMasked) { 0
286 // Mask needs to be copied to V0. ----
287 SDValue Mask = Node->getOperand(CurOp++); 0
288 Chain = CurDAG->getCopyToReg(Chain, DL, RISCV::V0, Mask, SDValue()); 0
289 Glue = Chain.getValue(1); 0
290 Operands.push_back(CurDAG->getRegister(RISCV::V0, Mask.getValueType())); 0
291 } ----
292 SDValue VL; 0
293 selectVLOp(Node->getOperand(CurOp++), VL); 0
294 Operands.push_back(VL); 0
295 ----
296 MVT XLenVT = Subtarget->getXLenVT(); 0
297 SDValue SEWOp = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Log2SEW, DL, XLenVT); 0
298 Operands.push_back(SEWOp); 0
299 ----
300 // At the IR layer, all the masked load intrinsics have policy operands, ----
301 // none of the others do. All have passthru operands. For our pseudos, ----
302 // all loads have policy operands. ----
303 if (IsLoad) { 0
304 uint64_t Policy = RISCVII::MASK_AGNOSTIC; 0
305 if (IsMasked) 0
306 Policy = Node->getConstantOperandVal(CurOp++); 0
307 SDValue PolicyOp = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Policy, DL, XLenVT); 0
308 Operands.push_back(PolicyOp); 0
309 } ----
310 ----
311 Operands.push_back(Chain); // Chain. 0
312 if (Glue) 0
313 Operands.push_back(Glue); 0
314 } 0

316 void RISCVDAGToDAGISel::selectVLSEG(SDNode *Node, bool IsMasked, 0
317 bool IsStrided) { ----
318 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
319 unsigned NF = Node->getNumValues() - 1; 0
320 MVT VT = Node->getSimpleValueType(0); 0
321 unsigned Log2SEW = Log2_32(VT.getScalarSizeInBits()); 0
322 RISCVII::VLMUL LMUL = RISCVTargetLowering::getLMUL(VT); 0
323 ----
324 unsigned CurOp = 2; 0
325 SmallVector Operands; 0
326 ----
327 SmallVector Regs(Node->op_begin() + CurOp, 0
328 Node->op_begin() + CurOp + NF); 0
329 SDValue Merge = createTuple(*CurDAG, Regs, NF, LMUL); 0
330 Operands.push_back(Merge); 0
331 CurOp += NF; 0
332 ----
333 addVectorLoadStoreOperands(Node, Log2SEW, DL, CurOp, IsMasked, IsStrided, 0
334 Operands, /*IsLoad=*/true); ----
335 ----
336 const RISCV::VLSEGPseudo *P = ----
337 RISCV::getVLSEGPseudo(NF, IsMasked, IsStrided, /*FF*/ false, Log2SEW, 0
338 static_cast(LMUL)); ----
339 MachineSDNode *Load = ----
340 CurDAG->getMachineNode(P->Pseudo, DL, MVT::Untyped, MVT::Other, Operands); 0
341 ----
342 if (auto *MemOp = dyn_cast(Node)) 0
343 CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(Load, {MemOp->getMemOperand()}); 0
344 ----
345 SDValue SuperReg = SDValue(Load, 0); 0
346 for (unsigned I = 0; I < NF; ++I) { 0
347 unsigned SubRegIdx = RISCVTargetLowering::getSubregIndexByMVT(VT, I); 0
348 ReplaceUses(SDValue(Node, I), 0
349 CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg(SubRegIdx, DL, VT, SuperReg)); 0
350 } ----
351 ----
352 ReplaceUses(SDValue(Node, NF), SDValue(Load, 1)); 0
353 CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(Node); 0
354 } 0

523 void RISCVDAGToDAGISel::selectVSETVLI(SDNode *Node) { 0
524 if (!Subtarget->hasVInstructions()) 0
525 return; 0
526 ----
527 assert(Node->getOpcode() == ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN && "Unexpected opcode"); 0
528 ----
529 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
530 MVT XLenVT = Subtarget->getXLenVT(); 0
531 ----
532 unsigned IntNo = Node->getConstantOperandVal(0); 0
533 ----
534 assert((IntNo == Intrinsic::riscv_vsetvli || 0
535 IntNo == Intrinsic::riscv_vsetvlimax) && ----
536 "Unexpected vsetvli intrinsic"); ----
537 ----
538 bool VLMax = IntNo == Intrinsic::riscv_vsetvlimax; 0
539 unsigned Offset = (VLMax ? 1 : 2); 0
540 ----
541 assert(Node->getNumOperands() == Offset + 2 && 0
542 "Unexpected number of operands"); ----
543 ----
544 unsigned SEW = ----
545 RISCVVType::decodeVSEW(Node->getConstantOperandVal(Offset) & 0x7); 0
546 RISCVII::VLMUL VLMul = static_cast( 0
547 Node->getConstantOperandVal(Offset + 1) & 0x7); 0
548 ----
549 unsigned VTypeI = RISCVVType::encodeVTYPE(VLMul, SEW, /*TailAgnostic*/ true, 0
550 /*MaskAgnostic*/ true); ----
551 SDValue VTypeIOp = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(VTypeI, DL, XLenVT); 0
552 ----
553 SDValue VLOperand; 0
554 unsigned Opcode = RISCV::PseudoVSETVLI; 0
555 if (VLMax || isAllOnesConstant(Node->getOperand(1))) { 0
556 VLOperand = CurDAG->getRegister(RISCV::X0, XLenVT); 0
557 Opcode = RISCV::PseudoVSETVLIX0; 0
558 } else { ----
559 VLOperand = Node->getOperand(1); 0
560 ----
561 if (auto *C = dyn_cast(VLOperand)) { 0
562 uint64_t AVL = C->getZExtValue(); 0
563 if (isUInt<5>(AVL)) { 0
564 SDValue VLImm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AVL, DL, XLenVT); 0
565 ReplaceNode(Node, CurDAG->getMachineNode(RISCV::PseudoVSETIVLI, DL, 0
566 XLenVT, VLImm, VTypeIOp)); ----
567 return; 0
568 } ----
569 } ----
570 } ----
571 ----
572 ReplaceNode(Node, 0
573 CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opcode, DL, XLenVT, VLOperand, VTypeIOp)); 0
574 } 0
575 ----
576 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::tryShrinkShlLogicImm(SDNode *Node) { 0
577 MVT VT = Node->getSimpleValueType(0); 0
578 unsigned Opcode = Node->getOpcode(); 0
579 assert((Opcode == ISD::AND || Opcode == ISD::OR || Opcode == ISD::XOR) && 0
580 "Unexpected opcode"); ----
581 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
582 ----
583 // For operations of the form (x << C1) op C2, check if we can use ----
584 // ANDI/ORI/XORI by transforming it into (x op (C2>>C1)) << C1. ----
585 SDValue N0 = Node->getOperand(0); 0
586 SDValue N1 = Node->getOperand(1); 0
587 ----
588 ConstantSDNode *Cst = dyn_cast(N1); 0
589 if (!Cst) 0
590 return false; 0
591 ----
592 int64_t Val = Cst->getSExtValue(); 0
593 ----
594 // Check if immediate can already use ANDI/ORI/XORI. ----
595 if (isInt<12>(Val)) 0
596 return false; 0
597 ----
598 SDValue Shift = N0; 0
599 ----
600 // If Val is simm32 and we have a sext_inreg from i32, then the binop ----
601 // produces at least 33 sign bits. We can peek through the sext_inreg and use ----
602 // a SLLIW at the end. ----
603 bool SignExt = false; 0
604 if (isInt<32>(Val) && N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG && 0
605 N0.hasOneUse() && cast(N0.getOperand(1))->getVT() == MVT::i32) { 0
606 SignExt = true; 0
607 Shift = N0.getOperand(0); 0
608 } ----
609 ----
610 if (Shift.getOpcode() != ISD::SHL || !Shift.hasOneUse()) 0
611 return false; 0
612 ----
613 ConstantSDNode *ShlCst = dyn_cast(Shift.getOperand(1)); 0
614 if (!ShlCst) 0
615 return false; 0
616 ----
617 uint64_t ShAmt = ShlCst->getZExtValue(); 0
618 ----
619 // Make sure that we don't change the operation by removing bits. ----
620 // This only matters for OR and XOR, AND is unaffected. ----
621 uint64_t RemovedBitsMask = maskTrailingOnes(ShAmt); 0
622 if (Opcode != ISD::AND && (Val & RemovedBitsMask) != 0) 0
623 return false; 0
624 ----
625 int64_t ShiftedVal = Val >> ShAmt; 0
626 if (!isInt<12>(ShiftedVal)) 0
627 return false; 0
628 ----
629 // If we peeked through a sext_inreg, make sure the shift is valid for SLLIW. ----
630 if (SignExt && ShAmt >= 32) 0
631 return false; 0
632 ----
633 // Ok, we can reorder to get a smaller immediate. ----
634 unsigned BinOpc; ----
635 switch (Opcode) { 0
636 default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected opcode"); 0
637 case ISD::AND: BinOpc = RISCV::ANDI; break; 0
638 case ISD::OR: BinOpc = RISCV::ORI; break; 0
639 case ISD::XOR: BinOpc = RISCV::XORI; break; 0
640 } ----
641 ----
642 unsigned ShOpc = SignExt ? RISCV::SLLIW : RISCV::SLLI; 0
643 ----
644 SDNode *BinOp = ----
645 CurDAG->getMachineNode(BinOpc, DL, VT, Shift.getOperand(0), 0
646 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ShiftedVal, DL, VT)); 0
647 SDNode *SLLI = ----
648 CurDAG->getMachineNode(ShOpc, DL, VT, SDValue(BinOp, 0), 0
649 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ShAmt, DL, VT)); 0
650 ReplaceNode(Node, SLLI); 0
651 return true; 0
652 } 0
653 ----
654 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::trySignedBitfieldExtract(SDNode *Node) { 0
655 // Only supported with XTHeadBb at the moment. ----
656 if (!Subtarget->hasVendorXTHeadBb()) 0
657 return false; 0
658 ----
659 auto *N1C = dyn_cast(Node->getOperand(1)); 0
660 if (!N1C) 0
661 return false; 0
662 ----
663 SDValue N0 = Node->getOperand(0); 0
664 if (!N0.hasOneUse()) 0
665 return false; 0
666 ----
667 auto BitfieldExtract = [&](SDValue N0, unsigned Msb, unsigned Lsb, SDLoc DL, 0
668 MVT VT) { ----
669 return CurDAG->getMachineNode(RISCV::TH_EXT, DL, VT, N0.getOperand(0), 0
670 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Msb, DL, VT), 0
671 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Lsb, DL, VT)); 0
672 }; 0
673 ----
674 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
675 MVT VT = Node->getSimpleValueType(0); 0
676 const unsigned RightShAmt = N1C->getZExtValue(); 0
677 ----
678 // Transform (sra (shl X, C1) C2) with C1 < C2 ----
679 // -> (TH.EXT X, msb, lsb) ----
680 if (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) { 0
681 auto *N01C = dyn_cast(N0->getOperand(1)); 0
682 if (!N01C) 0
683 return false; 0
684 ----
685 const unsigned LeftShAmt = N01C->getZExtValue(); 0
686 // Make sure that this is a bitfield extraction (i.e., the shift-right ----
687 // amount can not be less than the left-shift). ----
688 if (LeftShAmt > RightShAmt) 0
689 return false; 0
690 ----
691 const unsigned MsbPlusOne = VT.getSizeInBits() - LeftShAmt; 0
692 const unsigned Msb = MsbPlusOne - 1; 0
693 const unsigned Lsb = RightShAmt - LeftShAmt; 0
694 ----
695 SDNode *TH_EXT = BitfieldExtract(N0, Msb, Lsb, DL, VT); 0
696 ReplaceNode(Node, TH_EXT); 0
697 return true; 0
698 } ----
699 ----
700 // Transform (sra (sext_inreg X, _), C) -> ----
701 // (TH.EXT X, msb, lsb) ----
702 if (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG) { 0
703 unsigned ExtSize = ----
704 cast(N0.getOperand(1))->getVT().getSizeInBits(); 0
705 ----
706 // ExtSize of 32 should use sraiw via tablegen pattern. ----
707 if (ExtSize == 32) 0
708 return false; 0
709 ----
710 const unsigned Msb = ExtSize - 1; 0
711 const unsigned Lsb = RightShAmt; 0
712 ----
713 SDNode *TH_EXT = BitfieldExtract(N0, Msb, Lsb, DL, VT); 0
714 ReplaceNode(Node, TH_EXT); 0
715 return true; 0
716 } ----
717 ----
718 return false; 0
719 } 0
720 ----
721 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::tryIndexedLoad(SDNode *Node) { 0
722 // Target does not support indexed loads. ----
723 if (!Subtarget->hasVendorXTHeadMemIdx()) 0
724 return false; 0
725 ----
726 LoadSDNode *Ld = cast(Node); 0
727 ISD::MemIndexedMode AM = Ld->getAddressingMode(); 0
728 if (AM == ISD::UNINDEXED) 0
729 return false; 0
730 ----
731 const ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast(Ld->getOffset()); 0
732 if (!C) 0
733 return false; 0
734 ----
735 EVT LoadVT = Ld->getMemoryVT(); 0
736 bool IsPre = (AM == ISD::PRE_INC || AM == ISD::PRE_DEC); 0
737 bool IsPost = (AM == ISD::POST_INC || AM == ISD::POST_DEC); 0
738 int64_t Offset = C->getSExtValue(); 0
739 ----
740 // Convert decrements to increments by a negative quantity. ----
741 if (AM == ISD::PRE_DEC || AM == ISD::POST_DEC) 0
742 Offset = -Offset; 0
743 ----
744 // The constants that can be encoded in the THeadMemIdx instructions ----
745 // are of the form (sign_extend(imm5) << imm2). ----
746 int64_t Shift; ----
747 for (Shift = 0; Shift < 4; Shift++) 0
748 if (isInt<5>(Offset >> Shift) && ((Offset % (1LL << Shift)) == 0)) 0
749 break; 0
750 ----
751 // Constant cannot be encoded. ----
752 if (Shift == 4) 0
753 return false; 0
754 ----
755 bool IsZExt = (Ld->getExtensionType() == ISD::ZEXTLOAD); 0
756 unsigned Opcode; ----
757 if (LoadVT == MVT::i8 && IsPre) 0
758 Opcode = IsZExt ? RISCV::TH_LBUIB : RISCV::TH_LBIB; 0
759 else if (LoadVT == MVT::i8 && IsPost) 0
760 Opcode = IsZExt ? RISCV::TH_LBUIA : RISCV::TH_LBIA; 0
761 else if (LoadVT == MVT::i16 && IsPre) 0
762 Opcode = IsZExt ? RISCV::TH_LHUIB : RISCV::TH_LHIB; 0
763 else if (LoadVT == MVT::i16 && IsPost) 0
764 Opcode = IsZExt ? RISCV::TH_LHUIA : RISCV::TH_LHIA; 0
765 else if (LoadVT == MVT::i32 && IsPre) 0
766 Opcode = IsZExt ? RISCV::TH_LWUIB : RISCV::TH_LWIB; 0
767 else if (LoadVT == MVT::i32 && IsPost) 0
768 Opcode = IsZExt ? RISCV::TH_LWUIA : RISCV::TH_LWIA; 0
769 else if (LoadVT == MVT::i64 && IsPre) 0
770 Opcode = RISCV::TH_LDIB; 0
771 else if (LoadVT == MVT::i64 && IsPost) 0
772 Opcode = RISCV::TH_LDIA; 0
773 else ----
774 return false; 0
775 ----
776 EVT Ty = Ld->getOffset().getValueType(); 0
777 SDValue Ops[] = {Ld->getBasePtr(), 0
778 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Offset >> Shift, SDLoc(Node), Ty), 0
779 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Shift, SDLoc(Node), Ty), 0
780 Ld->getChain()}; 0
781 SDNode *New = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opcode, SDLoc(Node), Ld->getValueType(0), 0
782 Ld->getValueType(1), MVT::Other, Ops); ----
783 ----
784 MachineMemOperand *MemOp = cast(Node)->getMemOperand(); 0
785 CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(cast(New), {MemOp}); 0
786 ----
787 ReplaceNode(Node, New); 0
788 ----
789 return true; 0
790 } ----
791 ----
792 void RISCVDAGToDAGISel::Select(SDNode *Node) { 0
793 // If we have a custom node, we have already selected. ----
794 if (Node->isMachineOpcode()) { 0
795 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "== "; Node->dump(CurDAG); dbgs() << "\n"); 0
796 Node->setNodeId(-1); 0
797 return; 0
798 } ----
799 ----
800 // Instruction Selection not handled by the auto-generated tablegen selection ----
801 // should be handled here. ----
802 unsigned Opcode = Node->getOpcode(); 0
803 MVT XLenVT = Subtarget->getXLenVT(); 0
804 SDLoc DL(Node); 0
805 MVT VT = Node->getSimpleValueType(0); 0
806 ----
807 bool HasBitTest = Subtarget->hasStdExtZbs() || Subtarget->hasVendorXTHeadBs(); 0
808 ----
809 switch (Opcode) { 0
810 case ISD::Constant: { 0
811 assert(VT == Subtarget->getXLenVT() && "Unexpected VT"); 0
812 auto *ConstNode = cast(Node); 0
813 if (ConstNode->isZero()) { 0
814 SDValue New = ----
815 CurDAG->getCopyFromReg(CurDAG->getEntryNode(), DL, RISCV::X0, VT); 0
816 ReplaceNode(Node, New.getNode()); 0
817 return; 0
818 } ----
819 int64_t Imm = ConstNode->getSExtValue(); 0
820 // If the upper XLen-16 bits are not used, try to convert this to a simm12 ----
821 // by sign extending bit 15. ----
822 if (isUInt<16>(Imm) && isInt<12>(SignExtend64<16>(Imm)) && 0
823 hasAllHUsers(Node)) 0
824 Imm = SignExtend64<16>(Imm); 0
825 // If the upper 32-bits are not used try to convert this into a simm32 by ----
826 // sign extending bit 32. ----
827 if (!isInt<32>(Imm) && isUInt<32>(Imm) && hasAllWUsers(Node)) 0
828 Imm = SignExtend64<32>(Imm); 0
829 ----
830 ReplaceNode(Node, selectImm(CurDAG, DL, VT, Imm, *Subtarget).getNode()); 0
831 return; 0
832 } ----
833 case ISD::ConstantFP: { 0
834 const APFloat &APF = cast(Node)->getValueAPF(); 0
835 int FPImm = static_cast(TLI)->getLegalZfaFPImm( 0
836 APF, VT); ----
837 if (FPImm >= 0) { 0
838 unsigned Opc; ----
839 switch (VT.SimpleTy) { 0
840 default: 0
841 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected size"); 0
842 case MVT::f16: 0
843 Opc = RISCV::FLI_H; 0
844 break; 0
845 case MVT::f32: 0
846 Opc = RISCV::FLI_S; 0
847 break; 0
848 case MVT::f64: 0
849 Opc = RISCV::FLI_D; 0
850 break; 0
851 } ----
852 ----
853 SDNode *Res = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
854 Opc, DL, VT, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(FPImm, DL, XLenVT)); 0
855 ReplaceNode(Node, Res); 0
856 return; 0
857 } ----
858 ----
859 bool NegZeroF64 = APF.isNegZero() && VT == MVT::f64; 0
860 SDValue Imm; 0
861 // For +0.0 or f64 -0.0 we need to start from X0. For all others, we will ----
862 // create an integer immediate. ----
863 if (APF.isPosZero() || NegZeroF64) 0
864 Imm = CurDAG->getRegister(RISCV::X0, XLenVT); 0
865 else ----
866 Imm = selectImm(CurDAG, DL, XLenVT, APF.bitcastToAPInt().getSExtValue(), 0
867 *Subtarget); 0
868 ----
869 unsigned Opc; ----
870 switch (VT.SimpleTy) { 0
871 default: 0
872 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected size"); 0
873 case MVT::f16: 0
874 Opc = 0
875 Subtarget->hasStdExtZhinxOrZhinxmin() ? RISCV::COPY : RISCV::FMV_H_X; 0
876 break; 0
877 case MVT::f32: 0
878 Opc = Subtarget->hasStdExtZfinx() ? RISCV::COPY : RISCV::FMV_W_X; 0
879 break; 0
880 case MVT::f64: 0
881 // For RV32, we can't move from a GPR, we need to convert instead. This ----
882 // should only happen for +0.0 and -0.0. ----
883 assert((Subtarget->is64Bit() || APF.isZero()) && "Unexpected constant"); 0
884 bool HasZdinx = Subtarget->hasStdExtZdinx(); 0
885 if (Subtarget->is64Bit()) 0
886 Opc = HasZdinx ? RISCV::COPY : RISCV::FMV_D_X; 0
887 else ----
888 Opc = HasZdinx ? RISCV::FCVT_D_W_IN32X : RISCV::FCVT_D_W; 0
889 break; 0
890 } ----
891 ----
892 SDNode *Res = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, DL, VT, Imm); 0
893 ----
894 // For f64 -0.0, we need to insert a fneg.d idiom. ----
895 if (NegZeroF64) 0
896 Res = CurDAG->getMachineNode(RISCV::FSGNJN_D, DL, VT, SDValue(Res, 0), 0
897 SDValue(Res, 0)); ----
898 ----
899 ReplaceNode(Node, Res); 0
900 return; 0
901 } ----
902 case RISCVISD::SplitF64: { 0
903 if (!Subtarget->hasStdExtZfa()) 0
904 break; 0
905 assert(Subtarget->hasStdExtD() && !Subtarget->is64Bit() && 0
906 "Unexpected subtarget"); ----
907 ----
908 // With Zfa, lower to fmv.x.w and fmvh.x.d. ----
909 if (!SDValue(Node, 0).use_empty()) { 0
910 SDNode *Lo = CurDAG->getMachineNode(RISCV::FMV_X_W_FPR64, DL, VT, 0
911 Node->getOperand(0)); 0
912 ReplaceUses(SDValue(Node, 0), SDValue(Lo, 0)); 0
913 } ----
914 if (!SDValue(Node, 1).use_empty()) { 0
915 SDNode *Hi = CurDAG->getMachineNode(RISCV::FMVH_X_D, DL, VT, 0
916 Node->getOperand(0)); 0
917 ReplaceUses(SDValue(Node, 1), SDValue(Hi, 0)); 0
918 } ----
919 ----
920 CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(Node); 0
921 return; 0
922 } ----
923 case ISD::SHL: { 0
924 auto *N1C = dyn_cast(Node->getOperand(1)); 0
925 if (!N1C) 0
926 break; 0
927 SDValue N0 = Node->getOperand(0); 0
928 if (N0.getOpcode() != ISD::AND || !N0.hasOneUse() || 0
929 !isa(N0.getOperand(1))) 0
930 break; 0
931 unsigned ShAmt = N1C->getZExtValue(); 0
932 uint64_t Mask = N0.getConstantOperandVal(1); 0
933 ----
934 // Optimize (shl (and X, C2), C) -> (slli (srliw X, C3), C3+C) where C2 has ----
935 // 32 leading zeros and C3 trailing zeros. ----
936 if (ShAmt <= 32 && isShiftedMask_64(Mask)) { 0
937 unsigned XLen = Subtarget->getXLen(); 0
938 unsigned LeadingZeros = XLen - llvm::bit_width(Mask); 0
939 unsigned TrailingZeros = llvm::countr_zero(Mask); 0
940 if (TrailingZeros > 0 && LeadingZeros == 32) { 0
941 SDNode *SRLIW = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
942 RISCV::SRLIW, DL, VT, N0->getOperand(0), 0
943 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(TrailingZeros, DL, VT)); 0
944 SDNode *SLLI = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
945 RISCV::SLLI, DL, VT, SDValue(SRLIW, 0), ----
946 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(TrailingZeros + ShAmt, DL, VT)); 0
947 ReplaceNode(Node, SLLI); 0
948 return; 0
949 } ----
950 } ----
951 break; 0
952 } ----
953 case ISD::SRL: { 0
954 auto *N1C = dyn_cast(Node->getOperand(1)); 0
955 if (!N1C) 0
956 break; 0
957 SDValue N0 = Node->getOperand(0); 0
958 if (N0.getOpcode() != ISD::AND || !isa(N0.getOperand(1))) 0
959 break; 0
960 unsigned ShAmt = N1C->getZExtValue(); 0
961 uint64_t Mask = N0.getConstantOperandVal(1); 0
962 ----
963 // Optimize (srl (and X, C2), C) -> (slli (srliw X, C3), C3-C) where C2 has ----
964 // 32 leading zeros and C3 trailing zeros. ----
965 if (isShiftedMask_64(Mask) && N0.hasOneUse()) { 0
966 unsigned XLen = Subtarget->getXLen(); 0
967 unsigned LeadingZeros = XLen - llvm::bit_width(Mask); 0
968 unsigned TrailingZeros = llvm::countr_zero(Mask); 0
969 if (LeadingZeros == 32 && TrailingZeros > ShAmt) { 0
970 SDNode *SRLIW = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
971 RISCV::SRLIW, DL, VT, N0->getOperand(0), 0
972 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(TrailingZeros, DL, VT)); 0
973 SDNode *SLLI = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
974 RISCV::SLLI, DL, VT, SDValue(SRLIW, 0), ----
975 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(TrailingZeros - ShAmt, DL, VT)); 0
976 ReplaceNode(Node, SLLI); 0
977 return; 0
978 } ----
979 } ----
980 ----
981 // Optimize (srl (and X, C2), C) -> ----
982 // (srli (slli X, (XLen-C3), (XLen-C3) + C) ----
983 // Where C2 is a mask with C3 trailing ones. ----
984 // Taking into account that the C2 may have had lower bits unset by ----
985 // SimplifyDemandedBits. This avoids materializing the C2 immediate. ----
986 // This pattern occurs when type legalizing right shifts for types with ----
987 // less than XLen bits. ----
988 Mask |= maskTrailingOnes(ShAmt); 0
989 if (!isMask_64(Mask)) 0
990 break; 0
991 unsigned TrailingOnes = llvm::countr_one(Mask); 0
992 if (ShAmt >= TrailingOnes) 0
993 break; 0
994 // If the mask has 32 trailing ones, use SRLIW. ----
995 if (TrailingOnes == 32) { 0
996 SDNode *SRLIW = ----
997 CurDAG->getMachineNode(RISCV::SRLIW, DL, VT, N0->getOperand(0), 0
998 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ShAmt, DL, VT)); 0
999 ReplaceNode(Node, SRLIW); 0
1000 return; 0
1001 } ----
1002 ----
1003 // Only do the remaining transforms if the AND has one use. ----
1004 if (!N0.hasOneUse()) 0
1005 break; 0
1006 ----
1007 // If C2 is (1 << ShAmt) use bexti or th.tst if possible. ----
1008 if (HasBitTest && ShAmt + 1 == TrailingOnes) { 0
1009 SDNode *BEXTI = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1010 Subtarget->hasStdExtZbs() ? RISCV::BEXTI : RISCV::TH_TST, DL, VT, 0
1011 N0->getOperand(0), CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ShAmt, DL, VT)); 0
1012 ReplaceNode(Node, BEXTI); 0
1013 return; 0
1014 } ----
1015 ----
1016 unsigned LShAmt = Subtarget->getXLen() - TrailingOnes; 0
1017 SDNode *SLLI = ----
1018 CurDAG->getMachineNode(RISCV::SLLI, DL, VT, N0->getOperand(0), 0
1019 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(LShAmt, DL, VT)); 0
1020 SDNode *SRLI = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1021 RISCV::SRLI, DL, VT, SDValue(SLLI, 0), ----
1022 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(LShAmt + ShAmt, DL, VT)); 0
1023 ReplaceNode(Node, SRLI); 0
1024 return; 0
1025 } ----
1026 case ISD::SRA: { 0
1027 if (trySignedBitfieldExtract(Node)) 0
1028 return; 0
1029 ----
1030 // Optimize (sra (sext_inreg X, i16), C) -> ----
1031 // (srai (slli X, (XLen-16), (XLen-16) + C) ----
1032 // And (sra (sext_inreg X, i8), C) -> ----
1033 // (srai (slli X, (XLen-8), (XLen-8) + C) ----
1034 // This can occur when Zbb is enabled, which makes sext_inreg i16/i8 legal. ----
1035 // This transform matches the code we get without Zbb. The shifts are more ----
1036 // compressible, and this can help expose CSE opportunities in the sdiv by ----
1037 // constant optimization. ----
1038 auto *N1C = dyn_cast(Node->getOperand(1)); 0
1039 if (!N1C) 0
1040 break; 0
1041 SDValue N0 = Node->getOperand(0); 0
1042 if (N0.getOpcode() != ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG || !N0.hasOneUse()) 0
1043 break; 0
1044 unsigned ShAmt = N1C->getZExtValue(); 0
1045 unsigned ExtSize = ----
1046 cast(N0.getOperand(1))->getVT().getSizeInBits(); 0
1047 // ExtSize of 32 should use sraiw via tablegen pattern. ----
1048 if (ExtSize >= 32 || ShAmt >= ExtSize) 0
1049 break; ----
1050 unsigned LShAmt = Subtarget->getXLen() - ExtSize; 0
1051 SDNode *SLLI = ----
1052 CurDAG->getMachineNode(RISCV::SLLI, DL, VT, N0->getOperand(0), 0
1053 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(LShAmt, DL, VT)); 0
1054 SDNode *SRAI = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1055 RISCV::SRAI, DL, VT, SDValue(SLLI, 0), ----
1056 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(LShAmt + ShAmt, DL, VT)); 0
1057 ReplaceNode(Node, SRAI); 0
1058 return; 0
1059 } ----
1060 case ISD::OR: 0
1061 case ISD::XOR: ----
1062 if (tryShrinkShlLogicImm(Node)) 0
1063 return; 0
1064 ----
1065 break; 0
1066 case ISD::AND: { 0
1067 auto *N1C = dyn_cast(Node->getOperand(1)); 0
1068 if (!N1C) 0
1069 break; 0
1070 uint64_t C1 = N1C->getZExtValue(); 0
1071 const bool isC1Mask = isMask_64(C1); 0
1072 const bool isC1ANDI = isInt<12>(C1); 0
1073 ----
1074 SDValue N0 = Node->getOperand(0); 0
1075 ----
1076 auto tryUnsignedBitfieldExtract = [&](SDNode *Node, SDLoc DL, MVT VT, 0
1077 SDValue X, unsigned Msb, ----
1078 unsigned Lsb) { ----
1079 if (!Subtarget->hasVendorXTHeadBb()) 0
1080 return false; 0
1081 ----
1082 SDNode *TH_EXTU = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1083 RISCV::TH_EXTU, DL, VT, X, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Msb, DL, VT), 0
1084 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Lsb, DL, VT)); 0
1085 ReplaceNode(Node, TH_EXTU); 0
1086 return true; 0
1087 }; 0
1088 ----
1089 bool LeftShift = N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL; 0
1090 if (LeftShift || N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SRL) { 0
1091 auto *C = dyn_cast(N0.getOperand(1)); 0
1092 if (!C) 0
1093 break; 0
1094 unsigned C2 = C->getZExtValue(); 0
1095 unsigned XLen = Subtarget->getXLen(); 0
1096 assert((C2 > 0 && C2 < XLen) && "Unexpected shift amount!"); 0
1097 ----
1098 // Keep track of whether this is a c.andi. If we can't use c.andi, the ----
1099 // shift pair might offer more compression opportunities. ----
1100 // TODO: We could check for C extension here, but we don't have many lit ----
1101 // tests with the C extension enabled so not checking gets better ----
1102 // coverage. ----
1103 // TODO: What if ANDI faster than shift? ----
1104 bool IsCANDI = isInt<6>(N1C->getSExtValue()); 0
1105 ----
1106 // Clear irrelevant bits in the mask. ----
1107 if (LeftShift) 0
1108 C1 &= maskTrailingZeros(C2); 0
1109 else ----
1110 C1 &= maskTrailingOnes(XLen - C2); 0
1111 ----
1112 // Some transforms should only be done if the shift has a single use or ----
1113 // the AND would become (srli (slli X, 32), 32) ----
1114 bool OneUseOrZExtW = N0.hasOneUse() || C1 == UINT64_C(0xFFFFFFFF); 0
1115 ----
1116 SDValue X = N0.getOperand(0); 0
1117 ----
1118 // Turn (and (srl x, c2) c1) -> (srli (slli x, c3-c2), c3) if c1 is a mask ----
1119 // with c3 leading zeros. ----
1120 if (!LeftShift && isC1Mask) { 0
1121 unsigned Leading = XLen - llvm::bit_width(C1); 0
1122 if (C2 < Leading) { 0
1123 // If the number of leading zeros is C2+32 this can be SRLIW. ----
1124 if (C2 + 32 == Leading) { 0
1125 SDNode *SRLIW = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1126 RISCV::SRLIW, DL, VT, X, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(C2, DL, VT)); 0
1127 ReplaceNode(Node, SRLIW); 0
1128 return; 0
1129 } ----
1130 ----
1131 // (and (srl (sexti32 Y), c2), c1) -> (srliw (sraiw Y, 31), c3 - 32) ----
1132 // if c1 is a mask with c3 leading zeros and c2 >= 32 and c3-c2==1. ----
1133 // ----
1134 // This pattern occurs when (i32 (srl (sra 31), c3 - 32)) is type ----
1135 // legalized and goes through DAG combine. ----
1136 if (C2 >= 32 && (Leading - C2) == 1 && N0.hasOneUse() && 0
1137 X.getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG && 0
1138 cast(X.getOperand(1))->getVT() == MVT::i32) { 0
1139 SDNode *SRAIW = ----
1140 CurDAG->getMachineNode(RISCV::SRAIW, DL, VT, X.getOperand(0), 0
1141 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(31, DL, VT)); 0
1142 SDNode *SRLIW = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1143 RISCV::SRLIW, DL, VT, SDValue(SRAIW, 0), ----
1144 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Leading - 32, DL, VT)); 0
1145 ReplaceNode(Node, SRLIW); 0
1146 return; 0
1147 } ----
1148 ----
1149 // Try to use an unsigned bitfield extract (e.g., th.extu) if ----
1150 // available. ----
1151 // Transform (and (srl x, C2), C1) ----
1152 // -> ( x, msb, lsb) ----
1153 // ----
1154 // Make sure to keep this below the SRLIW cases, as we always want to ----
1155 // prefer the more common instruction. ----
1156 const unsigned Msb = llvm::bit_width(C1) + C2 - 1; 0
1157 const unsigned Lsb = C2; 0
1158 if (tryUnsignedBitfieldExtract(Node, DL, VT, X, Msb, Lsb)) 0
1159 return; 0
1160 ----
1161 // (srli (slli x, c3-c2), c3). ----
1162 // Skip if we could use (zext.w (sraiw X, C2)). ----
1163 bool Skip = Subtarget->hasStdExtZba() && Leading == 32 && 0
1164 X.getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG && 0
1165 cast(X.getOperand(1))->getVT() == MVT::i32; 0
1166 // Also Skip if we can use bexti or th.tst. ----
1167 Skip |= HasBitTest && Leading == XLen - 1; 0
1168 if (OneUseOrZExtW && !Skip) { 0
1169 SDNode *SLLI = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1170 RISCV::SLLI, DL, VT, X, ----
1171 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Leading - C2, DL, VT)); 0
1172 SDNode *SRLI = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1173 RISCV::SRLI, DL, VT, SDValue(SLLI, 0), ----
1174 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Leading, DL, VT)); 0
1175 ReplaceNode(Node, SRLI); 0
1176 return; 0
1177 } ----
1178 } ----
1179 } ----
1180 ----
1181 // Turn (and (shl x, c2), c1) -> (srli (slli c2+c3), c3) if c1 is a mask ----
1182 // shifted by c2 bits with c3 leading zeros. ----
1183 if (LeftShift && isShiftedMask_64(C1)) { 0
1184 unsigned Leading = XLen - llvm::bit_width(C1); 0
1185 ----
1186 if (C2 + Leading < XLen && 0
1187 C1 == (maskTrailingOnes(XLen - (C2 + Leading)) << C2)) { 0
1188 // Use slli.uw when possible. ----
1189 if ((XLen - (C2 + Leading)) == 32 && Subtarget->hasStdExtZba()) { 0
1190 SDNode *SLLI_UW = ----
1191 CurDAG->getMachineNode(RISCV::SLLI_UW, DL, VT, X, 0
1192 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(C2, DL, VT)); 0
1193 ReplaceNode(Node, SLLI_UW); 0
1194 return; 0
1195 } ----
1196 ----
1197 // (srli (slli c2+c3), c3) ----
1198 if (OneUseOrZExtW && !IsCANDI) { 0
1199 SDNode *SLLI = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1200 RISCV::SLLI, DL, VT, X, ----
1201 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(C2 + Leading, DL, VT)); 0
1202 SDNode *SRLI = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1203 RISCV::SRLI, DL, VT, SDValue(SLLI, 0), ----
1204 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Leading, DL, VT)); 0
1205 ReplaceNode(Node, SRLI); 0
1206 return; 0
1207 } ----
1208 } ----
1209 } ----
1210 ----
1211 // Turn (and (shr x, c2), c1) -> (slli (srli x, c2+c3), c3) if c1 is a ----
1212 // shifted mask with c2 leading zeros and c3 trailing zeros. ----
1213 if (!LeftShift && isShiftedMask_64(C1)) { 0
1214 unsigned Leading = XLen - llvm::bit_width(C1); 0
1215 unsigned Trailing = llvm::countr_zero(C1); 0
1216 if (Leading == C2 && C2 + Trailing < XLen && OneUseOrZExtW && 0
1217 !IsCANDI) { 0
1218 unsigned SrliOpc = RISCV::SRLI; 0
1219 // If the input is zexti32 we should use SRLIW. ----
1220 if (X.getOpcode() == ISD::AND && 0
1221 isa(X.getOperand(1)) && 0
1222 X.getConstantOperandVal(1) == UINT64_C(0xFFFFFFFF)) { 0
1223 SrliOpc = RISCV::SRLIW; 0
1224 X = X.getOperand(0); 0
1225 } ----
1226 SDNode *SRLI = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1227 SrliOpc, DL, VT, X, ----
1228 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(C2 + Trailing, DL, VT)); 0
1229 SDNode *SLLI = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1230 RISCV::SLLI, DL, VT, SDValue(SRLI, 0), ----
1231 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Trailing, DL, VT)); 0
1232 ReplaceNode(Node, SLLI); 0
1233 return; 0
1234 } ----
1235 // If the leading zero count is C2+32, we can use SRLIW instead of SRLI. ----
1236 if (Leading > 32 && (Leading - 32) == C2 && C2 + Trailing < 32 && 0
1237 OneUseOrZExtW && !IsCANDI) { 0
1238 SDNode *SRLIW = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1239 RISCV::SRLIW, DL, VT, X, ----
1240 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(C2 + Trailing, DL, VT)); 0
1241 SDNode *SLLI = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1242 RISCV::SLLI, DL, VT, SDValue(SRLIW, 0), ----
1243 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Trailing, DL, VT)); 0
1244 ReplaceNode(Node, SLLI); 0
1245 return; 0
1246 } ----
1247 } ----
1248 ----
1249 // Turn (and (shl x, c2), c1) -> (slli (srli x, c3-c2), c3) if c1 is a ----
1250 // shifted mask with no leading zeros and c3 trailing zeros. ----
1251 if (LeftShift && isShiftedMask_64(C1)) { 0
1252 unsigned Leading = XLen - llvm::bit_width(C1); 0
1253 unsigned Trailing = llvm::countr_zero(C1); 0
1254 if (Leading == 0 && C2 < Trailing && OneUseOrZExtW && !IsCANDI) { 0
1255 SDNode *SRLI = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1256 RISCV::SRLI, DL, VT, X, ----
1257 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Trailing - C2, DL, VT)); 0
1258 SDNode *SLLI = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1259 RISCV::SLLI, DL, VT, SDValue(SRLI, 0), ----
1260 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Trailing, DL, VT)); 0
1261 ReplaceNode(Node, SLLI); 0
1262 return; 0
1263 } ----
1264 // If we have (32-C2) leading zeros, we can use SRLIW instead of SRLI. ----
1265 if (C2 < Trailing && Leading + C2 == 32 && OneUseOrZExtW && !IsCANDI) { 0
1266 SDNode *SRLIW = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1267 RISCV::SRLIW, DL, VT, X, ----
1268 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Trailing - C2, DL, VT)); 0
1269 SDNode *SLLI = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
1270 RISCV::SLLI, DL, VT, SDValue(SRLIW, 0), ----
1271 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Trailing, DL, VT)); 0
1272 ReplaceNode(Node, SLLI); 0
1273 return; 0
1274 } ----
1275 } ----
1276 } ----
1277 ----
1278 // If C1 masks off the upper bits only (but can't be formed as an ----
1279 // ANDI), use an unsigned bitfield extract (e.g., th.extu), if ----
1280 // available. ----
1281 // Transform (and x, C1) ----
1282 // -> ( x, msb, lsb) ----
1283 if (isC1Mask && !isC1ANDI) { 0
1284 const unsigned Msb = llvm::bit_width(C1) - 1; 0
1285 if (tryUnsignedBitfieldExtract(Node, DL, VT, N0, Msb, 0)) 0
1286 return; 0
1287 } ----
1288 ----
1289 if (tryShrinkShlLogicImm(Node)) 0
1290 return; 0
1291 ----
1292 break; 0
1293 } ----
1294 case ISD::MUL: { 0
1295 // Special case for calculating (mul (and X, C2), C1) where the full product ----
1296 // fits in XLen bits. We can shift X left by the number of leading zeros in ----
1297 // C2 and shift C1 left by XLen-lzcnt(C2). This will ensure the final ----
1298 // product has XLen trailing zeros, putting it in the output of MULHU. This ----
1299 // can avoid materializing a constant in a register for C2. ----
1300 ----
1301 // RHS should be a constant. ----
1302 auto *N1C = dyn_cast(Node->getOperand(1)); 0
1303 if (!N1C || !N1C->hasOneUse()) 0
1304 break; 0
1305 ----
1306 // LHS should be an AND with constant. ----
1307 SDValue N0 = Node->getOperand(0); 0
1308 if (N0.getOpcode() != ISD::AND || !isa(N0.getOperand(1))) 0
1309 break; 0
1310 ----
1311 uint64_t C2 = cast(N0.getOperand(1))->getZExtValue(); 0
1312 ----
1313 // Constant should be a mask. ----
1314 if (!isMask_64(C2)) 0
1315 break; 0
1316 ----
1317 // If this can be an ANDI or ZEXT.H, don't do this if the ANDI/ZEXT has ----
1318 // multiple users or the constant is a simm12. This prevents inserting a ----
1319 // shift and still have uses of the AND/ZEXT. Shifting a simm12 will likely ----
1320 // make it more costly to materialize. Otherwise, using a SLLI might allow ----
1321 // it to be compressed. ----
1322 bool IsANDIOrZExt = ----
1323 isInt<12>(C2) || 0
1324 (C2 == UINT64_C(0xFFFF) && Subtarget->hasStdExtZbb()); 0
1325 // With XTHeadBb, we can use TH.EXTU. ----
1326 IsANDIOrZExt |= C2 == UINT64_C(0xFFFF) && Subtarget->hasVendorXTHeadBb(); 0
1327 if (IsANDIOrZExt && (isInt<12>(N1C->getSExtValue()) || !N0.hasOneUse())) 0
1328 break; 0
1329 // If this can be a ZEXT.w, don't do this if the ZEXT has multiple users or ----
1330 // the constant is a simm32. ----
1331 bool IsZExtW = C2 == UINT64_C(0xFFFFFFFF) && Subtarget->hasStdExtZba(); 0
1332 // With XTHeadBb, we can use TH.EXTU. ----
1333 IsZExtW |= C2 == UINT64_C(0xFFFFFFFF) && Subtarget->hasVendorXTHeadBb(); 0
1334 if (IsZExtW && (isInt<32>(N1C->getSExtValue()) || !N0.hasOneUse())) 0
1335 break; 0
1336 ----
1337 // We need to shift left the AND input and C1 by a total of XLen bits. ----
1338 ----
1339 // How far left do we need to shift the AND input? ----
1340 unsigned XLen = Subtarget->getXLen(); 0
1341 unsigned LeadingZeros = XLen - llvm::bit_width(C2); 0
1342 ----
1343 // The constant gets shifted by the remaining amount unless that would ----
1344 // shift bits out. ----
1345 uint64_t C1 = N1C->getZExtValue(); 0
1346 unsigned ConstantShift = XLen - LeadingZeros; 0
1347 if (ConstantShift > (XLen - llvm::bit_width(C1))) 0
1348 break; 0
1349 ----
1350 uint64_t ShiftedC1 = C1 << ConstantShift; 0
1351 // If this RV32, we need to sign extend the constant. ----
1352 if (XLen == 32) 0
1353 ShiftedC1 = SignExtend64<32>(ShiftedC1); 0
1354 ----
1355 // Create (mulhu (slli X, lzcnt(C2)), C1 << (XLen - lzcnt(C2))). ----
1356 SDNode *Imm = selectImm(CurDAG, DL, VT, ShiftedC1, *Subtarget).getNode(); 0
1357 SDNode *SLLI = ----
1358 CurDAG->getMachineNode(RISCV::SLLI, DL, VT, N0.getOperand(0), 0
1359 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(LeadingZeros, DL, VT)); 0
1360 SDNode *MULHU = CurDAG->getMachineNode(RISCV::MULHU, DL, VT, 0
1361 SDValue(SLLI, 0), SDValue(Imm, 0)); ----
1362 ReplaceNode(Node, MULHU); 0
1363 return; 0
1364 } ----
1365 case ISD::LOAD: { 0
1366 if (tryIndexedLoad(Node)) 0
1367 return; 0
1368 break; 0
1369 } ----
1370 case ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN: { 0
1371 unsigned IntNo = Node->getConstantOperandVal(0); 0
1372 switch (IntNo) { ----
1373 // By default we do not custom select any intrinsic. ----
1374 default: 0
1375 break; 0
1376 case Intrinsic::riscv_vmsgeu: 0
1377 case Intrinsic::riscv_vmsge: { ----
1378 SDValue Src1 = Node->getOperand(1); 0
1379 SDValue Src2 = Node->getOperand(2); 0
1380 bool IsUnsigned = IntNo == Intrinsic::riscv_vmsgeu; 0
1381 bool IsCmpUnsignedZero = false; 0
1382 // Only custom select scalar second operand. ----
1383 if (Src2.getValueType() != XLenVT) 0
1384 break; 0
1385 // Small constants are handled with patterns. ----
1386 if (auto *C = dyn_cast(Src2)) { 0
1387 int64_t CVal = C->getSExtValue(); 0
1388 if (CVal >= -15 && CVal <= 16) { 0
1389 if (!IsUnsigned || CVal != 0) 0
1390 break; ----
1391 IsCmpUnsignedZero = true; 0
1392 } ----
1393 } ----
1394 MVT Src1VT = Src1.getSimpleValueType(); 0
1395 unsigned VMSLTOpcode, VMNANDOpcode, VMSetOpcode; ----
1396 switch (RISCVTargetLowering::getLMUL(Src1VT)) { 0
1397 default: 0
1398 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected LMUL!"); 0
1399 #define CASE_VMSLT_VMNAND_VMSET_OPCODES(lmulenum, suffix, suffix_b) \ ----
1400 case RISCVII::VLMUL::lmulenum: \ ----
1401 VMSLTOpcode = IsUnsigned ? RISCV::PseudoVMSLTU_VX_##suffix \ ----
1402 : RISCV::PseudoVMSLT_VX_##suffix; \ ----
1403 VMNANDOpcode = RISCV::PseudoVMNAND_MM_##suffix; \ ----
1404 VMSetOpcode = RISCV::PseudoVMSET_M_##suffix_b; \ ----
1405 break; ----
1406 CASE_VMSLT_VMNAND_VMSET_OPCODES(LMUL_F8, MF8, B1) 0
1407 CASE_VMSLT_VMNAND_VMSET_OPCODES(LMUL_F4, MF4, B2) 0
1408 CASE_VMSLT_VMNAND_VMSET_OPCODES(LMUL_F2, MF2, B4) 0
1409 CASE_VMSLT_VMNAND_VMSET_OPCODES(LMUL_1, M1, B8) 0
1410 CASE_VMSLT_VMNAND_VMSET_OPCODES(LMUL_2, M2, B16) 0
1411 CASE_VMSLT_VMNAND_VMSET_OPCODES(LMUL_4, M4, B32) 0
1412 CASE_VMSLT_VMNAND_VMSET_OPCODES(LMUL_8, M8, B64) 0
1413 #undef CASE_VMSLT_VMNAND_VMSET_OPCODES ----
1414 } ----
1415 SDValue SEW = CurDAG->getTargetConstant( 0
1416 Log2_32(Src1VT.getScalarSizeInBits()), DL, XLenVT); 0
1417 SDValue VL; 0
1418 selectVLOp(Node->getOperand(3), VL); 0
1419 ----
1420 // If vmsgeu with 0 immediate, expand it to vmset. ----
1421 if (IsCmpUnsignedZero) { 0
1422 ReplaceNode(Node, CurDAG->getMachineNode(VMSetOpcode, DL, VT, VL, SEW)); 0
1423 return; 0
1424 } ----
1425 ----
1426 // Expand to ----
1427 // vmslt{u}.vx vd, va, x; vmnand.mm vd, vd, vd ----
1428 SDValue Cmp = SDValue( ----
1429 CurDAG->getMachineNode(VMSLTOpcode, DL, VT, {Src1, Src2, VL, SEW}), 0
1430 0); 0
1431 ReplaceNode(Node, CurDAG->getMachineNode(VMNANDOpcode, DL, VT, 0
1432 {Cmp, Cmp, VL, SEW})); ----
1433 return; 0
1434 } ----
1435 case Intrinsic::riscv_vmsgeu_mask: 0
1436 case Intrinsic::riscv_vmsge_mask: { ----
1437 SDValue Src1 = Node->getOperand(2); 0
1438 SDValue Src2 = Node->getOperand(3); 0
1439 bool IsUnsigned = IntNo == Intrinsic::riscv_vmsgeu_mask; 0
1440 bool IsCmpUnsignedZero = false; 0
1441 // Only custom select scalar second operand. ----
1442 if (Src2.getValueType() != XLenVT) 0
1443 break; 0
1444 // Small constants are handled with patterns. ----
1445 if (auto *C = dyn_cast(Src2)) { 0
1446 int64_t CVal = C->getSExtValue(); 0
1447 if (CVal >= -15 && CVal <= 16) { 0
1448 if (!IsUnsigned || CVal != 0) 0
1449 break; ----
1450 IsCmpUnsignedZero = true; 0
1451 } ----
1452 } ----
1453 MVT Src1VT = Src1.getSimpleValueType(); 0
1454 unsigned VMSLTOpcode, VMSLTMaskOpcode, VMXOROpcode, VMANDNOpcode, ----
1455 VMOROpcode; ----
1456 switch (RISCVTargetLowering::getLMUL(Src1VT)) { 0
1457 default: 0
1458 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected LMUL!"); 0
1459 #define CASE_VMSLT_OPCODES(lmulenum, suffix, suffix_b) \ ----
1460 case RISCVII::VLMUL::lmulenum: \ ----
1461 VMSLTOpcode = IsUnsigned ? RISCV::PseudoVMSLTU_VX_##suffix \ ----
1462 : RISCV::PseudoVMSLT_VX_##suffix; \ ----
1463 VMSLTMaskOpcode = IsUnsigned ? RISCV::PseudoVMSLTU_VX_##suffix##_MASK \ ----
1464 : RISCV::PseudoVMSLT_VX_##suffix##_MASK; \ ----
1465 break; ----
1466 CASE_VMSLT_OPCODES(LMUL_F8, MF8, B1) 0
1467 CASE_VMSLT_OPCODES(LMUL_F4, MF4, B2) 0
1468 CASE_VMSLT_OPCODES(LMUL_F2, MF2, B4) 0
1469 CASE_VMSLT_OPCODES(LMUL_1, M1, B8) 0
1470 CASE_VMSLT_OPCODES(LMUL_2, M2, B16) 0
1471 CASE_VMSLT_OPCODES(LMUL_4, M4, B32) 0
1472 CASE_VMSLT_OPCODES(LMUL_8, M8, B64) 0
1473 #undef CASE_VMSLT_OPCODES ----
1474 } ----
1475 // Mask operations use the LMUL from the mask type. ----
1476 switch (RISCVTargetLowering::getLMUL(VT)) { 0
1477 default: 0
1478 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected LMUL!"); 0
1479 #define CASE_VMXOR_VMANDN_VMOR_OPCODES(lmulenum, suffix) \ ----
1480 case RISCVII::VLMUL::lmulenum: \ ----
1481 VMXOROpcode = RISCV::PseudoVMXOR_MM_##suffix; \ ----
1482 VMANDNOpcode = RISCV::PseudoVMANDN_MM_##suffix; \ ----
1483 VMOROpcode = RISCV::PseudoVMOR_MM_##suffix; \ ----
1484 break; ----
1485 CASE_VMXOR_VMANDN_VMOR_OPCODES(LMUL_F8, MF8) 0
1486 CASE_VMXOR_VMANDN_VMOR_OPCODES(LMUL_F4, MF4) 0
1487 CASE_VMXOR_VMANDN_VMOR_OPCODES(LMUL_F2, MF2) 0
1488 CASE_VMXOR_VMANDN_VMOR_OPCODES(LMUL_1, M1) 0
1489 CASE_VMXOR_VMANDN_VMOR_OPCODES(LMUL_2, M2) 0
1490 CASE_VMXOR_VMANDN_VMOR_OPCODES(LMUL_4, M4) 0
1491 CASE_VMXOR_VMANDN_VMOR_OPCODES(LMUL_8, M8) 0
1492 #undef CASE_VMXOR_VMANDN_VMOR_OPCODES ----
1493 } ----
1494 SDValue SEW = CurDAG->getTargetConstant( 0
1495 Log2_32(Src1VT.getScalarSizeInBits()), DL, XLenVT); 0
1496 SDValue MaskSEW = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, XLenVT); 0
1497 SDValue VL; 0
1498 selectVLOp(Node->getOperand(5), VL); 0
1499 SDValue MaskedOff = Node->getOperand(1); 0
1500 SDValue Mask = Node->getOperand(4); 0
1501 ----
1502 // If vmsgeu_mask with 0 immediate, expand it to vmor mask, maskedoff. ----
1503 if (IsCmpUnsignedZero) { 0
1504 // We don't need vmor if the MaskedOff and the Mask are the same ----
1505 // value. ----
1506 if (Mask == MaskedOff) { 0
1507 ReplaceUses(Node, Mask.getNode()); 0
1508 return; 0
1509 } ----
1510 ReplaceNode(Node, 0
1511 CurDAG->getMachineNode(VMOROpcode, DL, VT, 0
1512 {Mask, MaskedOff, VL, MaskSEW})); ----
1513 return; 0
1514 } ----
1515 ----
1516 // If the MaskedOff value and the Mask are the same value use ----
1517 // vmslt{u}.vx vt, va, x; vmandn.mm vd, vd, vt ----
1518 // This avoids needing to copy v0 to vd before starting the next sequence. ----
1519 if (Mask == MaskedOff) { 0
1520 SDValue Cmp = SDValue( ----
1521 CurDAG->getMachineNode(VMSLTOpcode, DL, VT, {Src1, Src2, VL, SEW}), 0
1522 0); 0
1523 ReplaceNode(Node, CurDAG->getMachineNode(VMANDNOpcode, DL, VT, 0
1524 {Mask, Cmp, VL, MaskSEW})); ----
1525 return; 0
1526 } ----
1527 ----
1528 // Mask needs to be copied to V0. ----
1529 SDValue Chain = CurDAG->getCopyToReg(CurDAG->getEntryNode(), DL, 0
1530 RISCV::V0, Mask, SDValue()); ----
1531 SDValue Glue = Chain.getValue(1); 0
1532 SDValue V0 = CurDAG->getRegister(RISCV::V0, VT); 0
1533 ----
1534 // Otherwise use ----
1535 // vmslt{u}.vx vd, va, x, v0.t; vmxor.mm vd, vd, v0 ----
1536 // The result is mask undisturbed. ----
1537 // We use the same instructions to emulate mask agnostic behavior, because ----
1538 // the agnostic result can be either undisturbed or all 1. ----
1539 SDValue Cmp = SDValue( ----
1540 CurDAG->getMachineNode(VMSLTMaskOpcode, DL, VT, 0
1541 {MaskedOff, Src1, Src2, V0, VL, SEW, Glue}), ----
1542 0); 0
1543 // vmxor.mm vd, vd, v0 is used to update active value. ----
1544 ReplaceNode(Node, CurDAG->getMachineNode(VMXOROpcode, DL, VT, 0
1545 {Cmp, Mask, VL, MaskSEW})); ----
1546 return; 0
1547 } ----
1548 case Intrinsic::riscv_vsetvli: 0

1931 case ISD::BITCAST: { 0
1932 MVT SrcVT = Node->getOperand(0).getSimpleValueType(); 0
1933 // Just drop bitcasts between vectors if both are fixed or both are ----
1934 // scalable. ----
1935 if ((VT.isScalableVector() && SrcVT.isScalableVector()) || 0
1936 (VT.isFixedLengthVector() && SrcVT.isFixedLengthVector())) { 0

1943 case ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR: { 0
1944 SDValue V = Node->getOperand(0); 0
1945 SDValue SubV = Node->getOperand(1); 0
1946 SDLoc DL(SubV); 0
1947 auto Idx = Node->getConstantOperandVal(2); 0
1948 MVT SubVecVT = SubV.getSimpleValueType(); 0
1949 ----
1950 const RISCVTargetLowering &TLI = *Subtarget->getTargetLowering(); 0
1951 MVT SubVecContainerVT = SubVecVT; 0
1952 // Establish the correct scalable-vector types for any fixed-length type. ----
1953 if (SubVecVT.isFixedLengthVector()) 0
1954 SubVecContainerVT = TLI.getContainerForFixedLengthVector(SubVecVT); 0
1955 if (VT.isFixedLengthVector()) 0
1956 VT = TLI.getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT); 0
1957 ----
1958 const auto *TRI = Subtarget->getRegisterInfo(); 0
1959 unsigned SubRegIdx; ----
1960 std::tie(SubRegIdx, Idx) = 0
1961 RISCVTargetLowering::decomposeSubvectorInsertExtractToSubRegs( 0
1962 VT, SubVecContainerVT, Idx, TRI); 0
1963 ----
1964 // If the Idx hasn't been completely eliminated then this is a subvector ----
1965 // insert which doesn't naturally align to a vector register. These must ----
1966 // be handled using instructions to manipulate the vector registers. ----
1967 if (Idx != 0) 0
1968 break; 0
1969 ----
1970 RISCVII::VLMUL SubVecLMUL = RISCVTargetLowering::getLMUL(SubVecContainerVT); 0
1971 bool IsSubVecPartReg = SubVecLMUL == RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_F2 || 0
1972 SubVecLMUL == RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_F4 || 0
1973 SubVecLMUL == RISCVII::VLMUL::LMUL_F8; ----
1974 (void)IsSubVecPartReg; // Silence unused variable warning without asserts. ----
1975 assert((!IsSubVecPartReg || V.isUndef()) && 0
1976 "Expecting lowering to have created legal INSERT_SUBVECTORs when " ----
1977 "the subvector is smaller than a full-sized register"); ----
1978 ----
1979 // If we haven't set a SubRegIdx, then we must be going between ----
1980 // equally-sized LMUL groups (e.g. VR -> VR). This can be done as a copy. ----
1981 if (SubRegIdx == RISCV::NoSubRegister) { 0
1982 unsigned InRegClassID = RISCVTargetLowering::getRegClassIDForVecVT(VT); 0
1983 assert(RISCVTargetLowering::getRegClassIDForVecVT(SubVecContainerVT) == 0
1984 InRegClassID && ----
1985 "Unexpected subvector extraction"); ----
1986 SDValue RC = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(InRegClassID, DL, XLenVT); 0
1987 SDNode *NewNode = CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::COPY_TO_REGCLASS, 0
1988 DL, VT, SubV, RC); ----
1989 ReplaceNode(Node, NewNode); 0
1990 return; 0
1991 } ----
1992 ----
1993 SDValue Insert = CurDAG->getTargetInsertSubreg(SubRegIdx, DL, VT, V, SubV); 0
1994 ReplaceNode(Node, Insert.getNode()); 0
1995 return; 0
1996 } 0
1997 case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR: { 0
1998 SDValue V = Node->getOperand(0); 0
1999 auto Idx = Node->getConstantOperandVal(1); 0
2000 MVT InVT = V.getSimpleValueType(); 0
2001 SDLoc DL(V); 0
2002 ----
2003 const RISCVTargetLowering &TLI = *Subtarget->getTargetLowering(); 0
2004 MVT SubVecContainerVT = VT; 0
2005 // Establish the correct scalable-vector types for any fixed-length type. ----
2006 if (VT.isFixedLengthVector()) 0
2007 SubVecContainerVT = TLI.getContainerForFixedLengthVector(VT); 0
2008 if (InVT.isFixedLengthVector()) 0
2009 InVT = TLI.getContainerForFixedLengthVector(InVT); 0
2010 ----
2011 const auto *TRI = Subtarget->getRegisterInfo(); 0
2012 unsigned SubRegIdx; ----
2013 std::tie(SubRegIdx, Idx) = 0
2014 RISCVTargetLowering::decomposeSubvectorInsertExtractToSubRegs( 0
2015 InVT, SubVecContainerVT, Idx, TRI); 0
2016 ----
2017 // If the Idx hasn't been completely eliminated then this is a subvector ----
2018 // extract which doesn't naturally align to a vector register. These must ----
2019 // be handled using instructions to manipulate the vector registers. ----
2020 if (Idx != 0) 0
2021 break; 0
2022 ----
2023 // If we haven't set a SubRegIdx, then we must be going between ----
2024 // equally-sized LMUL types (e.g. VR -> VR). This can be done as a copy. ----
2025 if (SubRegIdx == RISCV::NoSubRegister) { 0
2026 unsigned InRegClassID = RISCVTargetLowering::getRegClassIDForVecVT(InVT); 0
2027 assert(RISCVTargetLowering::getRegClassIDForVecVT(SubVecContainerVT) == 0
2028 InRegClassID && ----
2029 "Unexpected subvector extraction"); ----
2030 SDValue RC = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(InRegClassID, DL, XLenVT); 0
2031 SDNode *NewNode = ----
2032 CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::COPY_TO_REGCLASS, DL, VT, V, RC); 0
2033 ReplaceNode(Node, NewNode); 0
2034 return; 0
2035 } ----
2036 ----
2037 SDValue Extract = CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg(SubRegIdx, DL, VT, V); 0
2038 ReplaceNode(Node, Extract.getNode()); 0
2039 return; 0
2040 } 0
2041 case RISCVISD::VMV_S_X_VL: 0
2042 case RISCVISD::VFMV_S_F_VL: ----
2043 case RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL: ----
2044 case RISCVISD::VFMV_V_F_VL: { ----
2045 // Try to match splat of a scalar load to a strided load with stride of x0. ----
2046 bool IsScalarMove = Node->getOpcode() == RISCVISD::VMV_S_X_VL || 0
2047 Node->getOpcode() == RISCVISD::VFMV_S_F_VL; 0
2048 if (!Node->getOperand(0).isUndef()) 0
2049 break; 0
2050 SDValue Src = Node->getOperand(1); 0
2051 auto *Ld = dyn_cast(Src); 0
2052 // Can't fold load update node because the second ----
2053 // output is used so that load update node can't be removed. ----
2054 if (!Ld || Ld->isIndexed()) 0
2055 break; 0
2056 EVT MemVT = Ld->getMemoryVT(); 0
2057 // The memory VT should be the same size as the element type. ----
2058 if (MemVT.getStoreSize() != VT.getVectorElementType().getStoreSize()) 0
2059 break; 0
2060 if (!IsProfitableToFold(Src, Node, Node) || 0
2061 !IsLegalToFold(Src, Node, Node, TM.getOptLevel())) 0
2062 break; 0
2063 ----
2064 SDValue VL; 0
2065 if (IsScalarMove) { 0
2066 // We could deal with more VL if we update the VSETVLI insert pass to ----
2067 // avoid introducing more VSETVLI. ----
2068 if (!isOneConstant(Node->getOperand(2))) 0
2069 break; 0
2070 selectVLOp(Node->getOperand(2), VL); 0
2071 } else ----
2072 selectVLOp(Node->getOperand(2), VL); 0
2073 ----
2074 unsigned Log2SEW = Log2_32(VT.getScalarSizeInBits()); 0
2075 SDValue SEW = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Log2SEW, DL, XLenVT); 0
2076 ----
2077 // If VL=1, then we don't need to do a strided load and can just do a ----
2078 // regular load. ----
2079 bool IsStrided = !isOneConstant(VL); 0
2080 ----
2081 // Only do a strided load if we have optimized zero-stride vector load. ----
2082 if (IsStrided && !Subtarget->hasOptimizedZeroStrideLoad()) 0
2083 break; 0
2084 ----
2085 SmallVector Operands = ----
2086 {CurDAG->getUNDEF(VT), Ld->getBasePtr()}; 0
2087 if (IsStrided) 0
2088 Operands.push_back(CurDAG->getRegister(RISCV::X0, XLenVT)); 0
2089 uint64_t Policy = RISCVII::MASK_AGNOSTIC | RISCVII::TAIL_AGNOSTIC; 0
2090 SDValue PolicyOp = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Policy, DL, XLenVT); 0
2091 Operands.append({VL, SEW, PolicyOp, Ld->getChain()}); 0
2092 ----
2093 RISCVII::VLMUL LMUL = RISCVTargetLowering::getLMUL(VT); 0
2094 const RISCV::VLEPseudo *P = RISCV::getVLEPseudo( 0
2095 /*IsMasked*/ false, IsStrided, /*FF*/ false, ----
2096 Log2SEW, static_cast(LMUL)); ----
2097 MachineSDNode *Load = ----
2098 CurDAG->getMachineNode(P->Pseudo, DL, {VT, MVT::Other}, Operands); 0
2099 // Update the chain. ----
2100 ReplaceUses(Src.getValue(1), SDValue(Load, 1)); 0
2101 // Record the mem-refs ----
2102 CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(Load, {Ld->getMemOperand()}); 0
2103 // Replace the splat with the vlse. ----
2104 ReplaceNode(Node, Load); 0
2105 return; 0
2106 } 0
2107 case ISD::PREFETCH: 0
2108 unsigned Locality = Node->getConstantOperandVal(3); 0
2109 if (Locality > 2) 0
2110 break; 0
2111 ----
2112 if (auto *LoadStoreMem = dyn_cast(Node)) { 0
2113 MachineMemOperand *MMO = LoadStoreMem->getMemOperand(); 0
2114 MMO->setFlags(MachineMemOperand::MONonTemporal); 0
2115 ----
2116 int NontemporalLevel = 0; 0
2117 switch (Locality) { ----
2118 case 0: 0
2119 NontemporalLevel = 3; // NTL.ALL 0
2120 break; 0
2121 case 1: 0
2122 NontemporalLevel = 1; // NTL.PALL 0
2123 break; 0
2124 case 2: 0
2125 NontemporalLevel = 0; // NTL.P1 0
2126 break; 0
2127 default: 0
2128 llvm_unreachable("unexpected locality value."); 0
2129 } ----
2130 ----
2131 if (NontemporalLevel & 0b1) 0
2132 MMO->setFlags(MONontemporalBit0); 0
2133 if (NontemporalLevel & 0b10) 0
2134 MMO->setFlags(MONontemporalBit1); 0
2135 } ----
2136 break; 0
2137 } ----
2138 ----
2139 // Select the default instruction. ----
2140 SelectCode(Node); 0
2141 } 0

2145 // Always produce a register and immediate operand, as expected by ----
