2205 // Fold constant addresses. ----
2206 static bool selectConstantAddr(SelectionDAG *CurDAG, const SDLoc &DL, 0
2207 const MVT VT, const RISCVSubtarget *Subtarget, ----
2208 SDValue Addr, SDValue &Base, SDValue &Offset) { ----
2209 if (!isa(Addr)) 0
2210 return false; 0
2211 ----
2212 int64_t CVal = cast(Addr)->getSExtValue(); 0
2213 ----
2214 // If the constant is a simm12, we can fold the whole constant and use X0 as ----
2215 // the base. If the constant can be materialized with LUI+simm12, use LUI as ----
2216 // the base. We can't use generateInstSeq because it favors LUI+ADDIW. ----
2217 int64_t Lo12 = SignExtend64<12>(CVal); 0
2218 int64_t Hi = (uint64_t)CVal - (uint64_t)Lo12; 0
2219 if (!Subtarget->is64Bit() || isInt<32>(Hi)) { 0
2220 if (Hi) { 0
2221 int64_t Hi20 = (Hi >> 12) & 0xfffff; 0
2222 Base = SDValue( 0
2223 CurDAG->getMachineNode(RISCV::LUI, DL, VT, 0
2224 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Hi20, DL, VT)), ----
2225 0); ----
2226 } else { ----
2227 Base = CurDAG->getRegister(RISCV::X0, VT); 0
2228 } ----
2229 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Lo12, DL, VT); 0
2230 return true; 0
2231 } ----
2232 ----
2233 // Ask how constant materialization would handle this constant. ----
2234 RISCVMatInt::InstSeq Seq = ----
2235 RISCVMatInt::generateInstSeq(CVal, Subtarget->getFeatureBits()); 0
2236 ----
2237 // If the last instruction would be an ADDI, we can fold its immediate and ----
2238 // emit the rest of the sequence as the base. ----
2239 if (Seq.back().getOpcode() != RISCV::ADDI) 0
2240 return false; 0
2241 Lo12 = Seq.back().getImm(); 0
2242 ----
2243 // Drop the last instruction. ----
2244 Seq.pop_back(); 0
2245 assert(!Seq.empty() && "Expected more instructions in sequence"); 0
2246 ----
2247 Base = selectImmSeq(CurDAG, DL, VT, Seq); 0
2248 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Lo12, DL, VT); 0
2249 return true; 0
2250 } 0
2251 ----
2252 // Is this ADD instruction only used as the base pointer of scalar loads and ----
2253 // stores? ----
2254 static bool isWorthFoldingAdd(SDValue Add) { 0
2255 for (auto *Use : Add->uses()) { 0
2256 if (Use->getOpcode() != ISD::LOAD && Use->getOpcode() != ISD::STORE && 0
2257 Use->getOpcode() != ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD && 0
2258 Use->getOpcode() != ISD::ATOMIC_STORE) 0
2259 return false; 0
2260 EVT VT = cast(Use)->getMemoryVT(); 0
2261 if (!VT.isScalarInteger() && VT != MVT::f16 && VT != MVT::f32 && 0
2262 VT != MVT::f64) 0
2263 return false; 0
2264 // Don't allow stores of the value. It must be used as the address. ----
2265 if (Use->getOpcode() == ISD::STORE && 0
2266 cast(Use)->getValue() == Add) 0
2267 return false; 0
2268 if (Use->getOpcode() == ISD::ATOMIC_STORE && 0
2269 cast(Use)->getVal() == Add) 0
2270 return false; 0
2271 } ----
2272 ----
2273 return true; 0
2274 } ----
2275 ----
2276 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::SelectAddrRegRegScale(SDValue Addr, 0
2277 unsigned MaxShiftAmount, ----
2278 SDValue &Base, SDValue &Index, ----
2279 SDValue &Scale) { ----
2280 EVT VT = Addr.getSimpleValueType(); 0
2281 auto UnwrapShl = [this, VT, MaxShiftAmount](SDValue N, SDValue &Index, 0
2282 SDValue &Shift) { 0
2283 uint64_t ShiftAmt = 0; 0
2284 Index = N; 0
2285 ----
2286 if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL && isa(N.getOperand(1))) { 0
2287 // Only match shifts by a value in range [0, MaxShiftAmount]. ----
2288 if (N.getConstantOperandVal(1) <= MaxShiftAmount) { 0
2289 Index = N.getOperand(0); 0
2290 ShiftAmt = N.getConstantOperandVal(1); 0
2291 } ----
2292 } ----
2293 ----
2294 Shift = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ShiftAmt, SDLoc(N), VT); 0
2295 return ShiftAmt != 0; 0
2296 }; 0
2297 ----
2298 if (Addr.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD) { 0
2299 if (auto *C1 = dyn_cast(Addr.getOperand(1))) { 0
2300 SDValue AddrB = Addr.getOperand(0); 0
2301 if (AddrB.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD && 0
2302 UnwrapShl(AddrB.getOperand(0), Index, Scale) && 0
2303 !isa(AddrB.getOperand(1)) && 0
2304 isInt<12>(C1->getSExtValue())) { 0
2305 // (add (add (shl A C2) B) C1) -> (add (add B C1) (shl A C2)) ----
2306 SDValue C1Val = ----
2307 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(C1->getZExtValue(), SDLoc(Addr), VT); 0
2308 Base = SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode(RISCV::ADDI, SDLoc(Addr), VT, 0
2309 AddrB.getOperand(1), C1Val), 0
2310 0); ----
2311 return true; 0
2312 } ----
2313 } else if (UnwrapShl(Addr.getOperand(0), Index, Scale)) { 0
2314 Base = Addr.getOperand(1); 0
2315 return true; 0
2316 } else { ----
2317 UnwrapShl(Addr.getOperand(1), Index, Scale); 0
2318 Base = Addr.getOperand(0); 0
2319 return true; 0
2320 } ----
2321 } else if (UnwrapShl(Addr, Index, Scale)) { 0
2322 EVT VT = Addr.getValueType(); 0
2323 Base = CurDAG->getRegister(RISCV::X0, VT); 0
2324 return true; 0
2325 } ----
2326 ----
2327 return false; 0
2328 } ----
2329 ----
2330 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::SelectAddrRegImm(SDValue Addr, SDValue &Base, 0
2331 SDValue &Offset, bool IsINX) { ----
2332 if (SelectAddrFrameIndex(Addr, Base, Offset)) 0
2333 return true; 0
2334 ----
2335 SDLoc DL(Addr); 0
2336 MVT VT = Addr.getSimpleValueType(); 0
2337 ----
2338 if (Addr.getOpcode() == RISCVISD::ADD_LO) { 0
2339 Base = Addr.getOperand(0); 0
2340 Offset = Addr.getOperand(1); 0
2341 return true; 0
2342 } ----
2343 ----
2344 int64_t RV32ZdinxRange = IsINX ? 4 : 0; 0
2345 if (CurDAG->isBaseWithConstantOffset(Addr)) { 0
2346 int64_t CVal = cast(Addr.getOperand(1))->getSExtValue(); 0
2347 if (isInt<12>(CVal) && isInt<12>(CVal + RV32ZdinxRange)) { 0
2348 Base = Addr.getOperand(0); 0
2349 if (Base.getOpcode() == RISCVISD::ADD_LO) { 0
2350 SDValue LoOperand = Base.getOperand(1); 0
2351 if (auto *GA = dyn_cast(LoOperand)) { 0
2352 // If the Lo in (ADD_LO hi, lo) is a global variable's address ----
2353 // (its low part, really), then we can rely on the alignment of that ----
2354 // variable to provide a margin of safety before low part can overflow ----
2355 // the 12 bits of the load/store offset. Check if CVal falls within ----
2356 // that margin; if so (low part + CVal) can't overflow. ----
2357 const DataLayout &DL = CurDAG->getDataLayout(); 0
2358 Align Alignment = commonAlignment( 0
2359 GA->getGlobal()->getPointerAlignment(DL), GA->getOffset()); 0
2360 if (CVal == 0 || Alignment > CVal) { 0
2361 int64_t CombinedOffset = CVal + GA->getOffset(); 0
2362 Base = Base.getOperand(0); 0
2363 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetGlobalAddress( 0
2364 GA->getGlobal(), SDLoc(LoOperand), LoOperand.getValueType(), 0
2365 CombinedOffset, GA->getTargetFlags()); ----
2366 return true; 0
2367 } ----
2368 } ----
2369 } ----
2370 ----
2371 if (auto *FIN = dyn_cast(Base)) 0
2372 Base = CurDAG->getTargetFrameIndex(FIN->getIndex(), VT); 0
2373 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(CVal, DL, VT); 0
2374 return true; 0
2375 } ----
2376 } ----
2377 ----
2378 // Handle ADD with large immediates. ----
2379 if (Addr.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD && isa(Addr.getOperand(1))) { 0
2380 int64_t CVal = cast(Addr.getOperand(1))->getSExtValue(); 0
2381 assert(!(isInt<12>(CVal) && isInt<12>(CVal + RV32ZdinxRange)) && 0
2382 "simm12 not already handled?"); ----
2383 ----
2384 // Handle immediates in the range [-4096,-2049] or [2048, 4094]. We can use ----
2385 // an ADDI for part of the offset and fold the rest into the load/store. ----
2386 // This mirrors the AddiPair PatFrag in RISCVInstrInfo.td. ----
2387 if (isInt<12>(CVal / 2) && isInt<12>(CVal - CVal / 2)) { 0
2388 int64_t Adj = CVal < 0 ? -2048 : 2047; 0
2389 Base = SDValue( 0
2390 CurDAG->getMachineNode(RISCV::ADDI, DL, VT, Addr.getOperand(0), 0
2391 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Adj, DL, VT)), 0
2392 0); ----
2393 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(CVal - Adj, DL, VT); 0
2394 return true; 0
2395 } ----
2396 ----
2397 // For larger immediates, we might be able to save one instruction from ----
2398 // constant materialization by folding the Lo12 bits of the immediate into ----
2399 // the address. We should only do this if the ADD is only used by loads and ----
2400 // stores that can fold the lo12 bits. Otherwise, the ADD will get iseled ----
2401 // separately with the full materialized immediate creating extra ----
2402 // instructions. ----
2403 if (isWorthFoldingAdd(Addr) && 0
2404 selectConstantAddr(CurDAG, DL, VT, Subtarget, Addr.getOperand(1), Base, 0
2405 Offset)) { ----
2406 // Insert an ADD instruction with the materialized Hi52 bits. ----
2407 Base = SDValue( 0
2408 CurDAG->getMachineNode(RISCV::ADD, DL, VT, Addr.getOperand(0), Base), 0
2409 0); ----
2410 return true; 0
2411 } ----
2412 } ----
2413 ----
2414 if (selectConstantAddr(CurDAG, DL, VT, Subtarget, Addr, Base, Offset)) 0
2415 return true; 0
2416 ----
2417 Base = Addr; 0
2418 Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, VT); 0
2419 return true; 0
2420 } 0
2421 ----
2422 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::selectShiftMask(SDValue N, unsigned ShiftWidth, 0
2423 SDValue &ShAmt) { ----
2424 ShAmt = N; 0
2425 ----
2426 // Shift instructions on RISC-V only read the lower 5 or 6 bits of the shift ----
2427 // amount. If there is an AND on the shift amount, we can bypass it if it ----
2428 // doesn't affect any of those bits. ----
2429 if (ShAmt.getOpcode() == ISD::AND && isa(ShAmt.getOperand(1))) { 0
2430 const APInt &AndMask = ShAmt.getConstantOperandAPInt(1); 0
2431 ----
2432 // Since the max shift amount is a power of 2 we can subtract 1 to make a ----
2433 // mask that covers the bits needed to represent all shift amounts. ----
2434 assert(isPowerOf2_32(ShiftWidth) && "Unexpected max shift amount!"); 0
2435 APInt ShMask(AndMask.getBitWidth(), ShiftWidth - 1); 0
2436 ----
2437 if (ShMask.isSubsetOf(AndMask)) { 0
2438 ShAmt = ShAmt.getOperand(0); 0
2439 } else { ----
2440 // SimplifyDemandedBits may have optimized the mask so try restoring any ----
2441 // bits that are known zero. ----
2442 KnownBits Known = CurDAG->computeKnownBits(ShAmt.getOperand(0)); 0
2443 if (!ShMask.isSubsetOf(AndMask | Known.Zero)) 0
2444 return true; 0
2445 ShAmt = ShAmt.getOperand(0); 0
2446 } 0
2447 } 0
2448 ----
2449 if (ShAmt.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD && 0
2450 isa(ShAmt.getOperand(1))) { 0
2451 uint64_t Imm = ShAmt.getConstantOperandVal(1); 0
2452 // If we are shifting by X+N where N == 0 mod Size, then just shift by X ----
2453 // to avoid the ADD. ----
2454 if (Imm != 0 && Imm % ShiftWidth == 0) { 0
2455 ShAmt = ShAmt.getOperand(0); 0
2456 return true; 0
2457 } ----
2458 } else if (ShAmt.getOpcode() == ISD::SUB && 0
2459 isa(ShAmt.getOperand(0))) { 0
2460 uint64_t Imm = ShAmt.getConstantOperandVal(0); 0
2461 // If we are shifting by N-X where N == 0 mod Size, then just shift by -X to ----
2462 // generate a NEG instead of a SUB of a constant. ----
2463 if (Imm != 0 && Imm % ShiftWidth == 0) { 0
2464 SDLoc DL(ShAmt); 0
2465 EVT VT = ShAmt.getValueType(); 0
2466 SDValue Zero = CurDAG->getRegister(RISCV::X0, VT); 0
2467 unsigned NegOpc = VT == MVT::i64 ? RISCV::SUBW : RISCV::SUB; 0
2468 MachineSDNode *Neg = CurDAG->getMachineNode(NegOpc, DL, VT, Zero, 0
2469 ShAmt.getOperand(1)); 0
2470 ShAmt = SDValue(Neg, 0); 0
2471 return true; 0
2472 } 0
2473 // If we are shifting by N-X where N == -1 mod Size, then just shift by ~X ----
2474 // to generate a NOT instead of a SUB of a constant. ----
2475 if (Imm % ShiftWidth == ShiftWidth - 1) { 0
2476 SDLoc DL(ShAmt); 0
2477 EVT VT = ShAmt.getValueType(); 0
2478 MachineSDNode *Not = ----
2479 CurDAG->getMachineNode(RISCV::XORI, DL, VT, ShAmt.getOperand(1), 0
2480 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(-1, DL, VT)); 0
2481 ShAmt = SDValue(Not, 0); 0
2482 return true; 0
2483 } 0
2484 } ----
2485 ----
2486 return true; 0
2487 } ----
2488 ----
2489 /// RISC-V doesn't have general instructions for integer setne/seteq, but we can ----
2490 /// check for equality with 0. This function emits instructions that convert the ----
2491 /// seteq/setne into something that can be compared with 0. ----
2492 /// \p ExpectedCCVal indicates the condition code to attempt to match (e.g. ----
2493 /// ISD::SETNE). ----
2494 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::selectSETCC(SDValue N, ISD::CondCode ExpectedCCVal, 0
2495 SDValue &Val) { ----
2496 assert(ISD::isIntEqualitySetCC(ExpectedCCVal) && 0
2497 "Unexpected condition code!"); ----
2498 ----
2499 // We're looking for a setcc. ----
2500 if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::SETCC) 0
2501 return false; 0
2502 ----
2503 // Must be an equality comparison. ----
2504 ISD::CondCode CCVal = cast(N->getOperand(2))->get(); 0
2505 if (CCVal != ExpectedCCVal) 0
2506 return false; 0
2507 ----
2508 SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0); 0
2509 SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1); 0
2510 ----
2511 if (!LHS.getValueType().isScalarInteger()) 0
2512 return false; 0
2513 ----
2514 // If the RHS side is 0, we don't need any extra instructions, return the LHS. ----
2515 if (isNullConstant(RHS)) { 0
2516 Val = LHS; 0
2517 return true; 0
2518 } ----
2519 ----
2520 SDLoc DL(N); 0
2521 ----
2522 if (auto *C = dyn_cast(RHS)) { 0
2523 int64_t CVal = C->getSExtValue(); 0
2524 // If the RHS is -2048, we can use xori to produce 0 if the LHS is -2048 and ----
2525 // non-zero otherwise. ----
2526 if (CVal == -2048) { 0
2527 Val = 0
2528 SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
2529 RISCV::XORI, DL, N->getValueType(0), LHS, ----
2530 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(CVal, DL, N->getValueType(0))), 0
2531 0); ----
2532 return true; 0
2533 } ----
2534 // If the RHS is [-2047,2048], we can use addi with -RHS to produce 0 if the ----
2535 // LHS is equal to the RHS and non-zero otherwise. ----
2536 if (isInt<12>(CVal) || CVal == 2048) { 0
2537 Val = 0
2538 SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
2539 RISCV::ADDI, DL, N->getValueType(0), LHS, ----
2540 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(-CVal, DL, N->getValueType(0))), 0
2541 0); ----
2542 return true; 0
2543 } ----
2544 } ----
2545 ----
2546 // If nothing else we can XOR the LHS and RHS to produce zero if they are ----
2547 // equal and a non-zero value if they aren't. ----
2548 Val = SDValue( 0
2549 CurDAG->getMachineNode(RISCV::XOR, DL, N->getValueType(0), LHS, RHS), 0); 0
2550 return true; 0
2551 } 0
2552 ----
2553 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::selectSExtBits(SDValue N, unsigned Bits, SDValue &Val) { 0
2554 if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG && 0
2555 cast(N.getOperand(1))->getVT().getSizeInBits() == Bits) { 0
2556 Val = N.getOperand(0); 0
2557 return true; 0
2558 } ----
2559 ----
2560 auto UnwrapShlSra = [](SDValue N, unsigned ShiftAmt) { 0
2561 if (N.getOpcode() != ISD::SRA || !isa(N.getOperand(1))) 0
2562 return N; 0
2563 ----
2564 SDValue N0 = N.getOperand(0); 0
2565 if (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL && isa(N0.getOperand(1)) && 0
2566 N.getConstantOperandVal(1) == ShiftAmt && 0
2567 N0.getConstantOperandVal(1) == ShiftAmt) 0
2568 return N0.getOperand(0); 0
2569 ----
2570 return N; 0
2571 }; ----
2572 ----
2573 MVT VT = N.getSimpleValueType(); 0
2574 if (CurDAG->ComputeNumSignBits(N) > (VT.getSizeInBits() - Bits)) { 0
2575 Val = UnwrapShlSra(N, VT.getSizeInBits() - Bits); 0
2576 return true; 0
2577 } ----
2578 ----
2579 return false; 0
2580 } ----
2581 ----
2582 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::selectZExtBits(SDValue N, unsigned Bits, SDValue &Val) { 0
2583 if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::AND) { 0
2584 auto *C = dyn_cast(N.getOperand(1)); 0
2585 if (C && C->getZExtValue() == maskTrailingOnes(Bits)) { 0
2586 Val = N.getOperand(0); 0
2587 return true; 0
2588 } ----
2589 } ----
2590 MVT VT = N.getSimpleValueType(); 0
2591 APInt Mask = APInt::getBitsSetFrom(VT.getSizeInBits(), Bits); 0
2592 if (CurDAG->MaskedValueIsZero(N, Mask)) { 0
2593 Val = N; 0
2594 return true; 0
2595 } ----
2596 ----
2597 return false; 0
2598 } 0
2599 ----
2600 /// Look for various patterns that can be done with a SHL that can be folded ----
2601 /// into a SHXADD. \p ShAmt contains 1, 2, or 3 and is set based on which ----
2602 /// SHXADD we are trying to match. ----
2603 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::selectSHXADDOp(SDValue N, unsigned ShAmt, 0
2604 SDValue &Val) { ----
2605 if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::AND && isa(N.getOperand(1))) { 0
2606 SDValue N0 = N.getOperand(0); 0
2607 ----
2608 bool LeftShift = N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL; 0
2609 if ((LeftShift || N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SRL) && 0
2610 isa(N0.getOperand(1))) { 0
2611 uint64_t Mask = N.getConstantOperandVal(1); 0
2612 unsigned C2 = N0.getConstantOperandVal(1); 0
2613 ----
2614 unsigned XLen = Subtarget->getXLen(); 0
2615 if (LeftShift) 0
2616 Mask &= maskTrailingZeros(C2); 0
2617 else ----
2618 Mask &= maskTrailingOnes(XLen - C2); 0
2619 ----
2620 // Look for (and (shl y, c2), c1) where c1 is a shifted mask with no ----
2621 // leading zeros and c3 trailing zeros. We can use an SRLI by c2+c3 ----
2622 // followed by a SHXADD with c3 for the X amount. ----
2623 if (isShiftedMask_64(Mask)) { 0
2624 unsigned Leading = XLen - llvm::bit_width(Mask); 0
2625 unsigned Trailing = llvm::countr_zero(Mask); 0
2626 if (LeftShift && Leading == 0 && C2 < Trailing && Trailing == ShAmt) { 0
2627 SDLoc DL(N); 0
2628 EVT VT = N.getValueType(); 0
2629 Val = SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
2630 RISCV::SRLI, DL, VT, N0.getOperand(0), 0
2631 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Trailing - C2, DL, VT)), 0
2632 0); ----
2633 return true; 0
2634 } 0
2635 // Look for (and (shr y, c2), c1) where c1 is a shifted mask with c2 ----
2636 // leading zeros and c3 trailing zeros. We can use an SRLI by C3 ----
2637 // followed by a SHXADD using c3 for the X amount. ----
2638 if (!LeftShift && Leading == C2 && Trailing == ShAmt) { 0
2639 SDLoc DL(N); 0
2640 EVT VT = N.getValueType(); 0
2641 Val = SDValue( 0
2642 CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
2643 RISCV::SRLI, DL, VT, N0.getOperand(0), 0
2644 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Leading + Trailing, DL, VT)), 0
2645 0); ----
2646 return true; 0
2647 } 0
2648 } ----
2649 } ----
2650 } ----
2651 ----
2652 bool LeftShift = N.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL; 0
2653 if ((LeftShift || N.getOpcode() == ISD::SRL) && 0
2654 isa(N.getOperand(1))) { 0
2655 SDValue N0 = N.getOperand(0); 0
2656 if (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::AND && N0.hasOneUse() && 0
2657 isa(N0.getOperand(1))) { 0
2658 uint64_t Mask = N0.getConstantOperandVal(1); 0
2659 if (isShiftedMask_64(Mask)) { 0
2660 unsigned C1 = N.getConstantOperandVal(1); 0
2661 unsigned XLen = Subtarget->getXLen(); 0
2662 unsigned Leading = XLen - llvm::bit_width(Mask); 0
2663 unsigned Trailing = llvm::countr_zero(Mask); 0
2664 // Look for (shl (and X, Mask), C1) where Mask has 32 leading zeros and ----
2665 // C3 trailing zeros. If C1+C3==ShAmt we can use SRLIW+SHXADD. ----
2666 if (LeftShift && Leading == 32 && Trailing > 0 && 0
2667 (Trailing + C1) == ShAmt) { 0
2668 SDLoc DL(N); 0
2669 EVT VT = N.getValueType(); 0
2670 Val = SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
2671 RISCV::SRLIW, DL, VT, N0.getOperand(0), 0
2672 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Trailing, DL, VT)), 0
2673 0); ----
2674 return true; 0
2675 } 0
2676 // Look for (srl (and X, Mask), C1) where Mask has 32 leading zeros and ----
2677 // C3 trailing zeros. If C3-C1==ShAmt we can use SRLIW+SHXADD. ----
2678 if (!LeftShift && Leading == 32 && Trailing > C1 && 0
2679 (Trailing - C1) == ShAmt) { 0
2680 SDLoc DL(N); 0
2681 EVT VT = N.getValueType(); 0
2682 Val = SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
2683 RISCV::SRLIW, DL, VT, N0.getOperand(0), 0
2684 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Trailing, DL, VT)), 0
2685 0); ----
2686 return true; 0
2687 } 0
2688 } ----
2689 } ----
2690 } ----
2691 ----
2692 return false; 0
2693 } ----
2694 ----
2695 /// Look for various patterns that can be done with a SHL that can be folded ----
2696 /// into a SHXADD_UW. \p ShAmt contains 1, 2, or 3 and is set based on which ----
2697 /// SHXADD_UW we are trying to match. ----
2698 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::selectSHXADD_UWOp(SDValue N, unsigned ShAmt, 0
2699 SDValue &Val) { ----
2700 if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::AND && isa(N.getOperand(1)) && 0
2701 N.hasOneUse()) { 0
2702 SDValue N0 = N.getOperand(0); 0
2703 if (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL && isa(N0.getOperand(1)) && 0
2704 N0.hasOneUse()) { 0
2705 uint64_t Mask = N.getConstantOperandVal(1); 0
2706 unsigned C2 = N0.getConstantOperandVal(1); 0
2707 ----
2708 Mask &= maskTrailingZeros(C2); 0
2709 ----
2710 // Look for (and (shl y, c2), c1) where c1 is a shifted mask with ----
2711 // 32-ShAmt leading zeros and c2 trailing zeros. We can use SLLI by ----
2712 // c2-ShAmt followed by SHXADD_UW with ShAmt for the X amount. ----
2713 if (isShiftedMask_64(Mask)) { 0
2714 unsigned Leading = llvm::countl_zero(Mask); 0
2715 unsigned Trailing = llvm::countr_zero(Mask); 0
2716 if (Leading == 32 - ShAmt && Trailing == C2 && Trailing > ShAmt) { 0
2717 SDLoc DL(N); 0
2718 EVT VT = N.getValueType(); 0
2719 Val = SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
2720 RISCV::SLLI, DL, VT, N0.getOperand(0), 0
2721 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(C2 - ShAmt, DL, VT)), 0
2722 0); ----
2723 return true; 0
2724 } 0
2725 } ----
2726 } ----
2727 } ----
2728 ----
2729 return false; 0
2730 } ----
2731 ----
2732 // Return true if all users of this SDNode* only consume the lower \p Bits. ----
2733 // This can be used to form W instructions for add/sub/mul/shl even when the ----
2734 // root isn't a sext_inreg. This can allow the ADDW/SUBW/MULW/SLLIW to CSE if ----
2735 // SimplifyDemandedBits has made it so some users see a sext_inreg and some ----
2736 // don't. The sext_inreg+add/sub/mul/shl will get selected, but still leave ----
2737 // the add/sub/mul/shl to become non-W instructions. By checking the users we ----
2738 // may be able to use a W instruction and CSE with the other instruction if ----
2739 // this has happened. We could try to detect that the CSE opportunity exists ----
2740 // before doing this, but that would be more complicated. ----
2741 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::hasAllNBitUsers(SDNode *Node, unsigned Bits, 0
2742 const unsigned Depth) const { ----
2743 assert((Node->getOpcode() == ISD::ADD || Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SUB || 0
2744 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::MUL || Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SHL || ----
2745 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SRL || Node->getOpcode() == ISD::AND || ----
2746 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::OR || Node->getOpcode() == ISD::XOR || ----
2747 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG || ----
2748 isa(Node) || Depth != 0) && ----
2749 "Unexpected opcode"); ----
2750 ----
2751 if (Depth >= SelectionDAG::MaxRecursionDepth) 0
2752 return false; 0
2753 ----
2754 for (auto UI = Node->use_begin(), UE = Node->use_end(); UI != UE; ++UI) { 0
2755 SDNode *User = *UI; 0
2756 // Users of this node should have already been instruction selected ----
2757 if (!User->isMachineOpcode()) 0
2758 return false; 0
2759 ----
2760 // TODO: Add more opcodes? ----
2761 switch (User->getMachineOpcode()) { 0
2762 default: 0
2763 return false; 0
2764 case RISCV::ADDW: 0
2765 case RISCV::ADDIW: ----
2766 case RISCV::SUBW: ----
2767 case RISCV::MULW: ----
2768 case RISCV::SLLW: ----
2769 case RISCV::SLLIW: ----
2770 case RISCV::SRAW: ----
2771 case RISCV::SRAIW: ----
2772 case RISCV::SRLW: ----
2773 case RISCV::SRLIW: ----
2774 case RISCV::DIVW: ----
2775 case RISCV::DIVUW: ----
2776 case RISCV::REMW: ----
2777 case RISCV::REMUW: ----
2778 case RISCV::ROLW: ----
2779 case RISCV::RORW: ----
2780 case RISCV::RORIW: ----
2781 case RISCV::CLZW: ----
2782 case RISCV::CTZW: ----
2783 case RISCV::CPOPW: ----
2784 case RISCV::SLLI_UW: ----
2785 case RISCV::FMV_W_X: ----
2786 case RISCV::FCVT_H_W: ----
2787 case RISCV::FCVT_H_WU: ----
2788 case RISCV::FCVT_S_W: ----
2789 case RISCV::FCVT_S_WU: ----
2790 case RISCV::FCVT_D_W: ----
2791 case RISCV::FCVT_D_WU: ----
2792 case RISCV::TH_REVW: ----
2793 case RISCV::TH_SRRIW: ----
2794 if (Bits < 32) 0
2795 return false; 0
2796 break; 0
2797 case RISCV::SLL: 0
2798 case RISCV::SRA: ----
2799 case RISCV::SRL: ----
2800 case RISCV::ROL: ----
2801 case RISCV::ROR: ----
2802 case RISCV::BSET: ----
2803 case RISCV::BCLR: ----
2804 case RISCV::BINV: ----
2805 // Shift amount operands only use log2(Xlen) bits. ----
2806 if (UI.getOperandNo() != 1 || Bits < Log2_32(Subtarget->getXLen())) 0
2807 return false; 0
2808 break; 0
2809 case RISCV::SLLI: 0
2810 // SLLI only uses the lower (XLen - ShAmt) bits. ----
2811 if (Bits < Subtarget->getXLen() - User->getConstantOperandVal(1)) 0
2812 return false; 0
2813 break; 0
2814 case RISCV::ANDI: 0
2815 if (Bits >= (unsigned)llvm::bit_width(User->getConstantOperandVal(1))) 0
2816 break; 0
2817 goto RecCheck; 0
2818 case RISCV::ORI: { 0
2819 uint64_t Imm = cast(User->getOperand(1))->getSExtValue(); 0
2820 if (Bits >= (unsigned)llvm::bit_width(~Imm)) 0
2821 break; 0
2822 [[fallthrough]]; ----
2823 } ----
2824 case RISCV::AND: ----
2825 case RISCV::OR: ----
2826 case RISCV::XOR: ----
2827 case RISCV::XORI: ----
2828 case RISCV::ANDN: ----
2829 case RISCV::ORN: ----
2830 case RISCV::XNOR: ----
2831 case RISCV::SH1ADD: ----
2832 case RISCV::SH2ADD: ----
2833 case RISCV::SH3ADD: ----
2834 RecCheck: 0
2835 if (hasAllNBitUsers(User, Bits, Depth + 1)) 0
2836 break; 0
2837 return false; 0
2838 case RISCV::SRLI: { 0
2839 unsigned ShAmt = User->getConstantOperandVal(1); 0
2840 // If we are shifting right by less than Bits, and users don't demand any ----
2841 // bits that were shifted into [Bits-1:0], then we can consider this as an ----
2842 // N-Bit user. ----
2843 if (Bits > ShAmt && hasAllNBitUsers(User, Bits - ShAmt, Depth + 1)) 0
2844 break; 0
2845 return false; 0
2846 } ----
2847 case RISCV::SEXT_B: 0
2848 case RISCV::PACKH: ----
2849 if (Bits < 8) 0
2850 return false; 0
2851 break; 0
2852 case RISCV::SEXT_H: 0
2853 case RISCV::FMV_H_X: ----
2854 case RISCV::ZEXT_H_RV32: ----
2855 case RISCV::ZEXT_H_RV64: ----
2856 case RISCV::PACKW: ----
2857 if (Bits < 16) 0
2858 return false; 0
2859 break; 0
2860 case RISCV::PACK: 0
2861 if (Bits < (Subtarget->getXLen() / 2)) 0
2862 return false; 0
2863 break; 0
2864 case RISCV::ADD_UW: 0
2865 case RISCV::SH1ADD_UW: ----
2866 case RISCV::SH2ADD_UW: ----
2867 case RISCV::SH3ADD_UW: ----
2868 // The first operand to add.uw/shXadd.uw is implicitly zero extended from ----
2869 // 32 bits. ----
2870 if (UI.getOperandNo() != 0 || Bits < 32) 0
2871 return false; 0
2872 break; 0
2873 case RISCV::SB: 0
2874 if (UI.getOperandNo() != 0 || Bits < 8) 0
2875 return false; 0
2876 break; 0
2877 case RISCV::SH: 0
2878 if (UI.getOperandNo() != 0 || Bits < 16) 0
2879 return false; 0
2880 break; 0
2881 case RISCV::SW: 0
2882 if (UI.getOperandNo() != 0 || Bits < 32) 0
2883 return false; 0
2884 break; 0
2885 } ----
2886 } ----
2887 ----
2888 return true; 0
2889 } ----
2890 ----
2891 // Select a constant that can be represented as (sign_extend(imm5) << imm2). ----
2892 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::selectSimm5Shl2(SDValue N, SDValue &Simm5, 0
2893 SDValue &Shl2) { ----
2894 if (auto *C = dyn_cast(N)) { 0
2895 int64_t Offset = C->getSExtValue(); 0
2896 int64_t Shift; ----
2897 for (Shift = 0; Shift < 4; Shift++) 0
2898 if (isInt<5>(Offset >> Shift) && ((Offset % (1LL << Shift)) == 0)) 0
2899 break; 0
2900 ----
2901 // Constant cannot be encoded. ----
2902 if (Shift == 4) 0
2903 return false; 0
2904 ----
2905 EVT Ty = N->getValueType(0); 0
2906 Simm5 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Offset >> Shift, SDLoc(N), Ty); 0
2907 Shl2 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Shift, SDLoc(N), Ty); 0
2908 return true; 0
2909 } ----
2910 ----
2911 return false; 0
2912 } ----
2913 ----
2914 // Select VL as a 5 bit immediate or a value that will become a register. This ----
2915 // allows us to choose betwen VSETIVLI or VSETVLI later. ----
2916 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::selectVLOp(SDValue N, SDValue &VL) { 0
2917 auto *C = dyn_cast(N); 0
2918 if (C && isUInt<5>(C->getZExtValue())) { 0
2919 VL = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(C->getZExtValue(), SDLoc(N), 0
2920 N->getValueType(0)); ----
2921 } else if (C && C->isAllOnes()) { 0
2922 // Treat all ones as VLMax. ----
2923 VL = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(RISCV::VLMaxSentinel, SDLoc(N), 0
2924 N->getValueType(0)); ----
2925 } else if (isa(N) && 0
2926 cast(N)->getReg() == RISCV::X0) { 0
2927 // All our VL operands use an operand that allows GPRNoX0 or an immediate ----
2928 // as the register class. Convert X0 to a special immediate to pass the ----
2929 // MachineVerifier. This is recognized specially by the vsetvli insertion ----
2930 // pass. ----
2931 VL = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(RISCV::VLMaxSentinel, SDLoc(N), 0
2932 N->getValueType(0)); ----
2933 } else { ----
2934 VL = N; 0
2935 } ----
2936 ----
2937 return true; 0
2938 } ----
2939 ----
2940 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::selectVSplat(SDValue N, SDValue &SplatVal) { 0
2941 if (N.getOpcode() != RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL || !N.getOperand(0).isUndef()) 0
2942 return false; 0
2943 assert(N.getNumOperands() == 3 && "Unexpected number of operands"); 0
2944 SplatVal = N.getOperand(1); 0
2945 return true; 0
2946 } ----
2947 ----
2948 using ValidateFn = bool (*)(int64_t); ----
2949 ----
2950 static bool selectVSplatSimmHelper(SDValue N, SDValue &SplatVal, 0
2951 SelectionDAG &DAG, ----
2952 const RISCVSubtarget &Subtarget, ----
2953 ValidateFn ValidateImm) { ----
2954 if (N.getOpcode() != RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL || !N.getOperand(0).isUndef() || 0
2955 !isa(N.getOperand(1))) 0
2956 return false; 0
2957 assert(N.getNumOperands() == 3 && "Unexpected number of operands"); 0
2958 ----
2959 int64_t SplatImm = ----
2960 cast(N.getOperand(1))->getSExtValue(); 0
2961 ----
2962 // The semantics of RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL is that when the operand ----
2963 // type is wider than the resulting vector element type: an implicit ----
2964 // truncation first takes place. Therefore, perform a manual ----
2965 // truncation/sign-extension in order to ignore any truncated bits and catch ----
2966 // any zero-extended immediate. ----
2967 // For example, we wish to match (i8 -1) -> (XLenVT 255) as a simm5 by first ----
2968 // sign-extending to (XLenVT -1). ----
2969 MVT XLenVT = Subtarget.getXLenVT(); 0
2970 assert(XLenVT == N.getOperand(1).getSimpleValueType() && 0
2971 "Unexpected splat operand type"); ----
2972 MVT EltVT = N.getSimpleValueType().getVectorElementType(); 0
2973 if (EltVT.bitsLT(XLenVT)) 0
2974 SplatImm = SignExtend64(SplatImm, EltVT.getSizeInBits()); 0
2975 ----
2976 if (!ValidateImm(SplatImm)) 0
2977 return false; 0
2978 ----
2979 SplatVal = DAG.getTargetConstant(SplatImm, SDLoc(N), XLenVT); 0
2980 return true; 0
2981 } ----
2982 ----
2983 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::selectVSplatSimm5(SDValue N, SDValue &SplatVal) { 0
2984 return selectVSplatSimmHelper(N, SplatVal, *CurDAG, *Subtarget, 0
2985 [](int64_t Imm) { return isInt<5>(Imm); }); 0
2986 } ----
2987 ----
2988 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::selectVSplatSimm5Plus1(SDValue N, SDValue &SplatVal) { 0
2989 return selectVSplatSimmHelper( 0
2990 N, SplatVal, *CurDAG, *Subtarget, 0
2991 [](int64_t Imm) { return (isInt<5>(Imm) && Imm != -16) || Imm == 16; }); 0
2992 } ----
2993 ----
2994 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::selectVSplatSimm5Plus1NonZero(SDValue N, 0
2995 SDValue &SplatVal) { ----
2996 return selectVSplatSimmHelper( 0
2997 N, SplatVal, *CurDAG, *Subtarget, [](int64_t Imm) { 0
2998 return Imm != 0 && ((isInt<5>(Imm) && Imm != -16) || Imm == 16); 0
2999 }); 0
3000 } ----
3001 ----
3002 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::selectVSplatUimm(SDValue N, unsigned Bits, 0
3003 SDValue &SplatVal) { ----
3004 if (N.getOpcode() != RISCVISD::VMV_V_X_VL || !N.getOperand(0).isUndef() || 0
3005 !isa(N.getOperand(1))) 0
3006 return false; 0
3007 ----
3008 int64_t SplatImm = ----
3009 cast(N.getOperand(1))->getSExtValue(); 0
3010 ----
3011 if (!isUIntN(Bits, SplatImm)) 0
3012 return false; 0
3013 ----
3014 SplatVal = 0
3015 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(SplatImm, SDLoc(N), Subtarget->getXLenVT()); 0

3017 return true; 0
3018 } ----
3019 ----
3020 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::selectLow8BitsVSplat(SDValue N, SDValue &SplatVal) { 0
3021 // Truncates are custom lowered during legalization. ----
3022 auto IsTrunc = [this](SDValue N) { 0
3023 if (N->getOpcode() != RISCVISD::TRUNCATE_VECTOR_VL) 0
3024 return false; 0
3025 SDValue VL; 0
3026 selectVLOp(N->getOperand(2), VL); 0
3027 // Any vmset_vl is ok, since any bits past VL are undefined and we can ----
3028 // assume they are set. ----
3029 return N->getOperand(1).getOpcode() == RISCVISD::VMSET_VL && 0
3030 isa(VL) && 0
3031 cast(VL)->getSExtValue() == RISCV::VLMaxSentinel; 0
3032 }; 0
3033 ----
3034 // We can have multiple nested truncates, so unravel them all if needed. ----
3035 while (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND || 0
3036 N->getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND || IsTrunc(N)) { 0
3037 if (!N.hasOneUse() || 0
3038 N.getValueType().getSizeInBits().getKnownMinValue() < 8) 0
3039 return false; 0
3040 N = N->getOperand(0); 0
3041 } ----
3042 ----
3043 return selectVSplat(N, SplatVal); 0
3044 } ----
3045 ----
3046 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::selectFPImm(SDValue N, SDValue &Imm) { 0
3047 ConstantFPSDNode *CFP = dyn_cast(N.getNode()); 0
3048 if (!CFP) 0
3049 return false; 0
3050 const APFloat &APF = CFP->getValueAPF(); 0
3051 // td can handle +0.0 already. ----
3052 if (APF.isPosZero()) 0
3053 return false; 0
3054 ----
3055 MVT VT = CFP->getSimpleValueType(0); 0
3056 ----
3057 if (static_cast(TLI)->getLegalZfaFPImm(APF, 0
3058 VT) >= 0) 0
3059 return false; 0
3060 ----
3061 MVT XLenVT = Subtarget->getXLenVT(); 0
3062 if (VT == MVT::f64 && !Subtarget->is64Bit()) { 0
3063 assert(APF.isNegZero() && "Unexpected constant."); 0
3064 return false; 0
3065 } ----
3066 SDLoc DL(N); 0
3067 Imm = selectImm(CurDAG, DL, XLenVT, APF.bitcastToAPInt().getSExtValue(), 0
3068 *Subtarget); 0
3069 return true; 0
3070 } 0
3071 ----
3072 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::selectRVVSimm5(SDValue N, unsigned Width, 0
3073 SDValue &Imm) { ----
3074 if (auto *C = dyn_cast(N)) { 0
3075 int64_t ImmVal = SignExtend64(C->getSExtValue(), Width); 0
3076 ----
3077 if (!isInt<5>(ImmVal)) 0
3078 return false; 0
3079 ----
3080 Imm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmVal, SDLoc(N), Subtarget->getXLenVT()); 0
3081 return true; 0
3082 } ----
3083 ----
3084 return false; 0
3085 } ----
3086 ----
3087 // Try to remove sext.w if the input is a W instruction or can be made into ----
3088 // a W instruction cheaply. ----
3089 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::doPeepholeSExtW(SDNode *N) { 0
3090 // Look for the sext.w pattern, addiw rd, rs1, 0. ----
3091 if (N->getMachineOpcode() != RISCV::ADDIW || 0
3092 !isNullConstant(N->getOperand(1))) 0
3093 return false; 0
3094 ----
3095 SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0); 0
3096 if (!N0.isMachineOpcode()) 0
3097 return false; 0
3098 ----
3099 switch (N0.getMachineOpcode()) { 0
3100 default: 0
3101 break; 0
3102 case RISCV::ADD: 0
3103 case RISCV::ADDI: ----
3104 case RISCV::SUB: ----
3105 case RISCV::MUL: ----
3106 case RISCV::SLLI: { ----
3107 // Convert sext.w+add/sub/mul to their W instructions. This will create ----
3108 // a new independent instruction. This improves latency. ----
3109 unsigned Opc; ----
3110 switch (N0.getMachineOpcode()) { 0
3111 default: 0
3112 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected opcode!"); 0
3113 case RISCV::ADD: Opc = RISCV::ADDW; break; 0
3114 case RISCV::ADDI: Opc = RISCV::ADDIW; break; 0
3115 case RISCV::SUB: Opc = RISCV::SUBW; break; 0
3116 case RISCV::MUL: Opc = RISCV::MULW; break; 0
3117 case RISCV::SLLI: Opc = RISCV::SLLIW; break; 0
3118 } ----
3119 ----
3120 SDValue N00 = N0.getOperand(0); 0
3121 SDValue N01 = N0.getOperand(1); 0
3122 ----
3123 // Shift amount needs to be uimm5. ----
3124 if (N0.getMachineOpcode() == RISCV::SLLI && 0
3125 !isUInt<5>(cast(N01)->getSExtValue())) 0
3126 break; 0
3127 ----
3128 SDNode *Result = ----
3129 CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0), 0
3130 N00, N01); ----
3131 ReplaceUses(N, Result); 0
3132 return true; 0
3133 } ----
3134 case RISCV::ADDW: 0
3135 case RISCV::ADDIW: ----
3136 case RISCV::SUBW: ----
3137 case RISCV::MULW: ----
3138 case RISCV::SLLIW: ----
3139 case RISCV::PACKW: ----
3140 case RISCV::TH_MULAW: ----
3141 case RISCV::TH_MULAH: ----
3142 case RISCV::TH_MULSW: ----
3143 case RISCV::TH_MULSH: ----
3144 // Result is already sign extended just remove the sext.w. ----
3145 // NOTE: We only handle the nodes that are selected with hasAllWUsers. ----
3146 ReplaceUses(N, N0.getNode()); 0
3147 return true; 0
3148 } ----
3149 ----
3150 return false; 0
3151 } ----
3152 ----
3153 static bool usesAllOnesMask(SDValue MaskOp, SDValue GlueOp) { 0
3154 // Check that we're using V0 as a mask register. ----
3155 if (!isa(MaskOp) || 0
3156 cast(MaskOp)->getReg() != RISCV::V0) 0
3157 return false; 0
3158 ----
3159 // The glued user defines V0. ----
3160 const auto *Glued = GlueOp.getNode(); 0
3161 ----
3162 if (!Glued || Glued->getOpcode() != ISD::CopyToReg) 0
3163 return false; 0
3164 ----
3165 // Check that we're defining V0 as a mask register. ----
3166 if (!isa(Glued->getOperand(1)) || 0
3167 cast(Glued->getOperand(1))->getReg() != RISCV::V0) 0
3168 return false; 0
3169 ----
3170 // Check the instruction defining V0; it needs to be a VMSET pseudo. ----
3171 SDValue MaskSetter = Glued->getOperand(2); 0
3172 ----
3173 const auto IsVMSet = [](unsigned Opc) { 0
3174 return Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMSET_M_B1 || Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMSET_M_B16 || 0
3175 Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMSET_M_B2 || Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMSET_M_B32 || 0
3176 Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMSET_M_B4 || Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMSET_M_B64 || 0
3177 Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMSET_M_B8; 0
3178 }; ----
3179 ----
3180 // TODO: Check that the VMSET is the expected bitwidth? The pseudo has ----
3181 // undefined behaviour if it's the wrong bitwidth, so we could choose to ----
3182 // assume that it's all-ones? Same applies to its VL. ----
3183 return MaskSetter->isMachineOpcode() && 0
3184 IsVMSet(MaskSetter.getMachineOpcode()); 0
3185 } ----
3186 ----
3187 // Return true if we can make sure mask of N is all-ones mask. ----
3188 static bool usesAllOnesMask(SDNode *N, unsigned MaskOpIdx) { 0
3189 return usesAllOnesMask(N->getOperand(MaskOpIdx), 0
3190 N->getOperand(N->getNumOperands() - 1)); 0
3191 } ----
3192 ----
3193 static bool isImplicitDef(SDValue V) { 0
3194 return V.isMachineOpcode() && 0
3195 V.getMachineOpcode() == TargetOpcode::IMPLICIT_DEF; 0
3196 } ----
3197 ----
3198 // Optimize masked RVV pseudo instructions with a known all-ones mask to their ----
3199 // corresponding "unmasked" pseudo versions. The mask we're interested in will ----
3200 // take the form of a V0 physical register operand, with a glued ----
3201 // register-setting instruction. ----
3202 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::doPeepholeMaskedRVV(SDNode *N) { 0
3203 const RISCV::RISCVMaskedPseudoInfo *I = ----
3204 RISCV::getMaskedPseudoInfo(N->getMachineOpcode()); 0
3205 if (!I) 0
3206 return false; 0
3207 ----
3208 unsigned MaskOpIdx = I->MaskOpIdx; 0
3209 if (!usesAllOnesMask(N, MaskOpIdx)) 0
3210 return false; 0
3211 ----
3212 // There are two classes of pseudos in the table - compares and ----
3213 // everything else. See the comment on RISCVMaskedPseudo for details. ----
3214 const unsigned Opc = I->UnmaskedPseudo; 0
3215 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = TII->get(Opc); 0
3216 const bool UseTUPseudo = RISCVII::hasVecPolicyOp(MCID.TSFlags); 0
3217 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
3218 const MCInstrDesc &MaskedMCID = TII->get(N->getMachineOpcode()); 0
3219 assert(RISCVII::hasVecPolicyOp(MaskedMCID.TSFlags) == 0
3220 RISCVII::hasVecPolicyOp(MCID.TSFlags) && ----
3221 "Masked and unmasked pseudos are inconsistent"); ----
3222 const bool HasTiedDest = RISCVII::isFirstDefTiedToFirstUse(MCID); 0
3223 assert(UseTUPseudo == HasTiedDest && "Unexpected pseudo structure"); 0
3224 #endif ----
3225 ----
3226 SmallVector Ops; 0
3227 // Skip the merge operand at index 0 if !UseTUPseudo. ----
3228 for (unsigned I = !UseTUPseudo, E = N->getNumOperands(); I != E; I++) { 0
3229 // Skip the mask, and the Glue. ----
3230 SDValue Op = N->getOperand(I); 0
3231 if (I == MaskOpIdx || Op.getValueType() == MVT::Glue) 0
3232 continue; 0
3233 Ops.push_back(Op); 0
3234 } ----
3235 ----
3236 // Transitively apply any node glued to our new node. ----
3237 const auto *Glued = N->getGluedNode(); 0
3238 if (auto *TGlued = Glued->getGluedNode()) 0
3239 Ops.push_back(SDValue(TGlued, TGlued->getNumValues() - 1)); 0
3240 ----
3241 SDNode *Result = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, SDLoc(N), N->getVTList(), Ops); 0
3242 Result->setFlags(N->getFlags()); 0
3243 ReplaceUses(N, Result); 0
3244 ----
3245 return true; 0
3246 } 0
3247 ----
3248 static bool IsVMerge(SDNode *N) { 0
3249 unsigned Opc = N->getMachineOpcode(); 0
3250 return Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMERGE_VVM_MF8 || 0
3251 Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMERGE_VVM_MF4 || 0
3252 Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMERGE_VVM_MF2 || 0
3253 Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMERGE_VVM_M1 || 0
3254 Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMERGE_VVM_M2 || 0
3255 Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMERGE_VVM_M4 || Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMERGE_VVM_M8; 0
3256 } ----
3257 ----
3258 static bool IsVMv(SDNode *N) { 0
3259 unsigned Opc = N->getMachineOpcode(); 0
3260 return Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMV_V_V_MF8 || Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMV_V_V_MF4 || 0
3261 Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMV_V_V_MF2 || Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMV_V_V_M1 || 0
3262 Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMV_V_V_M2 || Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMV_V_V_M4 || 0
3263 Opc == RISCV::PseudoVMV_V_V_M8; 0
3264 } ----
3265 ----
3266 static unsigned GetVMSetForLMul(RISCVII::VLMUL LMUL) { 0
3267 switch (LMUL) { 0
3268 case RISCVII::LMUL_F8: 0
3269 return RISCV::PseudoVMSET_M_B1; 0
3270 case RISCVII::LMUL_F4: 0
3271 return RISCV::PseudoVMSET_M_B2; 0
3272 case RISCVII::LMUL_F2: 0
3273 return RISCV::PseudoVMSET_M_B4; 0
3274 case RISCVII::LMUL_1: 0
3275 return RISCV::PseudoVMSET_M_B8; 0
3276 case RISCVII::LMUL_2: 0
3277 return RISCV::PseudoVMSET_M_B16; 0
3278 case RISCVII::LMUL_4: 0
3279 return RISCV::PseudoVMSET_M_B32; 0
3280 case RISCVII::LMUL_8: 0
3281 return RISCV::PseudoVMSET_M_B64; 0
3282 case RISCVII::LMUL_RESERVED: 0
3283 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected LMUL"); 0
3284 } ----
3285 llvm_unreachable("Unknown VLMUL enum"); 0
3286 } ----
3287 ----
3288 // Try to fold away VMERGE_VVM instructions. We handle these cases: ----
3289 // -Masked TU VMERGE_VVM combined with an unmasked TA instruction instruction ----
3290 // folds to a masked TU instruction. VMERGE_VVM must have have merge operand ----
3291 // same as false operand. ----
3292 // -Masked TA VMERGE_VVM combined with an unmasked TA instruction fold to a ----
3293 // masked TA instruction. ----
3294 // -Unmasked TU VMERGE_VVM combined with a masked MU TA instruction folds to ----
3295 // masked TU instruction. Both instructions must have the same merge operand. ----
3296 // VMERGE_VVM must have have merge operand same as false operand. ----
3297 // Note: The VMERGE_VVM forms above (TA, and TU) refer to the policy implied, ----
3298 // not the pseudo name. That is, a TA VMERGE_VVM can be either the _TU pseudo ----
3299 // form with an IMPLICIT_DEF passthrough operand or the unsuffixed (TA) pseudo ----
3300 // form. ----
3301 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::performCombineVMergeAndVOps(SDNode *N) { 0
3302 SDValue Merge, False, True, VL, Mask, Glue; 0
3303 // A vmv.v.v is equivalent to a vmerge with an all-ones mask. ----
3304 if (IsVMv(N)) { 0
3305 Merge = N->getOperand(0); 0
3306 False = N->getOperand(0); 0
3307 True = N->getOperand(1); 0
3308 VL = N->getOperand(2); 0
3309 // A vmv.v.v won't have a Mask or Glue, instead we'll construct an all-ones ----
3310 // mask later below. ----
3311 } else { ----
3312 assert(IsVMerge(N)); 0
3313 Merge = N->getOperand(0); 0
3314 False = N->getOperand(1); 0
3315 True = N->getOperand(2); 0
3316 Mask = N->getOperand(3); 0
3317 VL = N->getOperand(4); 0
3318 // We always have a glue node for the mask at v0. ----
3319 Glue = N->getOperand(N->getNumOperands() - 1); 0
3320 } ----
3321 assert(!Mask || cast(Mask)->getReg() == RISCV::V0); 0
3322 assert(!Glue || Glue.getValueType() == MVT::Glue); 0
3323 ----
3324 // We require that either merge and false are the same, or that merge ----
3325 // is undefined. ----
3326 if (Merge != False && !isImplicitDef(Merge)) 0
3327 return false; 0
3328 ----
3329 assert(True.getResNo() == 0 && 0
3330 "Expect True is the first output of an instruction."); ----
3331 ----
3332 // Need N is the exactly one using True. ----
3333 if (!True.hasOneUse()) 0
3334 return false; 0
3335 ----
3336 if (!True.isMachineOpcode()) 0
3337 return false; 0
3338 ----
3339 unsigned TrueOpc = True.getMachineOpcode(); 0
3340 const MCInstrDesc &TrueMCID = TII->get(TrueOpc); 0
3341 uint64_t TrueTSFlags = TrueMCID.TSFlags; 0
3342 bool HasTiedDest = RISCVII::isFirstDefTiedToFirstUse(TrueMCID); 0
3343 ----
3344 bool IsMasked = false; 0
3345 const RISCV::RISCVMaskedPseudoInfo *Info = ----
3346 RISCV::lookupMaskedIntrinsicByUnmasked(TrueOpc); 0
3347 if (!Info && HasTiedDest) { 0
3348 Info = RISCV::getMaskedPseudoInfo(TrueOpc); 0
3349 IsMasked = true; 0
3350 } ----
3351 ----
3352 if (!Info) 0
3353 return false; 0
3354 ----
3355 if (HasTiedDest && !isImplicitDef(True->getOperand(0))) { 0
3356 // The vmerge instruction must be TU. ----
3357 // FIXME: This could be relaxed, but we need to handle the policy for the ----
3358 // resulting op correctly. ----
3359 if (isImplicitDef(Merge)) 0
3360 return false; 0
3361 SDValue MergeOpTrue = True->getOperand(0); 0
3362 // Both the vmerge instruction and the True instruction must have the same ----
3363 // merge operand. ----
3364 if (False != MergeOpTrue) 0
3365 return false; 0
3366 } ----
3367 ----
3368 if (IsMasked) { 0
3369 assert(HasTiedDest && "Expected tied dest"); 0
3370 // The vmerge instruction must be TU. ----
3371 if (isImplicitDef(Merge)) 0
3372 return false; 0
3373 // The vmerge instruction must have an all 1s mask since we're going to keep ----
3374 // the mask from the True instruction. ----
3375 // FIXME: Support mask agnostic True instruction which would have an ----
3376 // undef merge operand. ----
3377 if (Mask && !usesAllOnesMask(Mask, Glue)) 0
3378 return false; 0
3379 } ----
3380 ----
3381 // Skip if True has side effect. ----
3382 // TODO: Support vleff and vlsegff. ----
3383 if (TII->get(TrueOpc).hasUnmodeledSideEffects()) 0
3384 return false; 0
3385 ----
3386 // The last operand of a masked instruction may be glued. ----
3387 bool HasGlueOp = True->getGluedNode() != nullptr; 0
3388 ----
3389 // The chain operand may exist either before the glued operands or in the last ----
3390 // position. ----
3391 unsigned TrueChainOpIdx = True.getNumOperands() - HasGlueOp - 1; 0
3392 bool HasChainOp = ----
3393 True.getOperand(TrueChainOpIdx).getValueType() == MVT::Other; 0
3394 ----
3395 if (HasChainOp) { 0
3396 // Avoid creating cycles in the DAG. We must ensure that none of the other ----
3397 // operands depend on True through it's Chain. ----
3398 SmallVector LoopWorklist; 0
3399 SmallPtrSet Visited; 0
3400 LoopWorklist.push_back(False.getNode()); 0
3401 if (Mask) 0
3402 LoopWorklist.push_back(Mask.getNode()); 0
3403 LoopWorklist.push_back(VL.getNode()); 0
3404 if (Glue) 0
3405 LoopWorklist.push_back(Glue.getNode()); 0
3406 if (SDNode::hasPredecessorHelper(True.getNode(), Visited, LoopWorklist)) 0
3407 return false; 0
3408 } 0
3409 ----
3410 // The vector policy operand may be present for masked intrinsics ----
3411 bool HasVecPolicyOp = RISCVII::hasVecPolicyOp(TrueTSFlags); 0
3412 unsigned TrueVLIndex = ----
3413 True.getNumOperands() - HasVecPolicyOp - HasChainOp - HasGlueOp - 2; 0
3414 SDValue TrueVL = True.getOperand(TrueVLIndex); 0
3415 SDValue SEW = True.getOperand(TrueVLIndex + 1); 0
3416 ----
3417 auto GetMinVL = [](SDValue LHS, SDValue RHS) { 0
3418 if (LHS == RHS) 0
3419 return LHS; 0
3420 if (isAllOnesConstant(LHS)) 0
3421 return RHS; 0
3422 if (isAllOnesConstant(RHS)) 0
3423 return LHS; 0
3424 auto *CLHS = dyn_cast(LHS); 0
3425 auto *CRHS = dyn_cast(RHS); 0
3426 if (!CLHS || !CRHS) 0
3427 return SDValue(); 0
3428 return CLHS->getZExtValue() <= CRHS->getZExtValue() ? LHS : RHS; 0
3429 }; ----
3430 ----
3431 // Because N and True must have the same merge operand (or True's operand is ----
3432 // implicit_def), the "effective" body is the minimum of their VLs. ----
3433 VL = GetMinVL(TrueVL, VL); 0
3434 if (!VL) 0
3435 return false; 0
3436 ----
3437 // If we end up changing the VL or mask of True, then we need to make sure it ----
3438 // doesn't raise any observable fp exceptions, since changing the active ----
3439 // elements will affect how fflags is set. ----
3440 if (TrueVL != VL || !IsMasked) 0
3441 if (mayRaiseFPException(True.getNode()) && 0
3442 !True->getFlags().hasNoFPExcept()) 0
3443 return false; 0
3444 ----
3445 SDLoc DL(N); 0
3446 ----
3447 // From the preconditions we checked above, we know the mask and thus glue ----
3448 // for the result node will be taken from True. ----
3449 if (IsMasked) { 0
3450 Mask = True->getOperand(Info->MaskOpIdx); 0
3451 Glue = True->getOperand(True->getNumOperands() - 1); 0
3452 assert(Glue.getValueType() == MVT::Glue); 0
3453 } ----
3454 // If we end up using the vmerge mask the vmerge is actually a vmv.v.v, create ----
3455 // an all-ones mask to use. ----
3456 else if (IsVMv(N)) { 0
3457 unsigned TSFlags = TII->get(N->getMachineOpcode()).TSFlags; 0
3458 unsigned VMSetOpc = GetVMSetForLMul(RISCVII::getLMul(TSFlags)); 0
3459 ElementCount EC = N->getValueType(0).getVectorElementCount(); 0
3460 MVT MaskVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i1, EC); 0
3461 ----
3462 SDValue AllOnesMask = ----
3463 SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode(VMSetOpc, DL, MaskVT, VL, SEW), 0); 0
3464 SDValue MaskCopy = CurDAG->getCopyToReg(CurDAG->getEntryNode(), DL, 0
3465 RISCV::V0, AllOnesMask, SDValue()); ----
3466 Mask = CurDAG->getRegister(RISCV::V0, MaskVT); 0
3467 Glue = MaskCopy.getValue(1); 0
3468 } ----
3469 ----
3470 unsigned MaskedOpc = Info->MaskedPseudo; 0
3471 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
3472 const MCInstrDesc &MaskedMCID = TII->get(MaskedOpc); 0
3473 assert(RISCVII::hasVecPolicyOp(MaskedMCID.TSFlags) && 0
3474 "Expected instructions with mask have policy operand."); ----
3475 assert(MaskedMCID.getOperandConstraint(MaskedMCID.getNumDefs(), 0
3476 MCOI::TIED_TO) == 0 && ----
3477 "Expected instructions with mask have a tied dest."); ----
3478 #endif ----
3479 ----
3480 uint64_t Policy = isImplicitDef(Merge) ? RISCVII::TAIL_AGNOSTIC : /*TUMU*/ 0; 0
3481 SDValue PolicyOp = ----
3482 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Policy, DL, Subtarget->getXLenVT()); 0
3483 ----
3484 ----
3485 SmallVector Ops; 0
3486 Ops.push_back(False); 0
3487 ----
3488 const bool HasRoundingMode = RISCVII::hasRoundModeOp(TrueTSFlags); 0
3489 const unsigned NormalOpsEnd = TrueVLIndex - IsMasked - HasRoundingMode; 0
3490 assert(!IsMasked || NormalOpsEnd == Info->MaskOpIdx); 0
3491 Ops.append(True->op_begin() + HasTiedDest, True->op_begin() + NormalOpsEnd); 0
3492 ----
3493 Ops.push_back(Mask); 0
3494 ----
3495 // For unmasked "VOp" with rounding mode operand, that is interfaces like ----
3496 // (..., rm, vl) or (..., rm, vl, policy). ----
3497 // Its masked version is (..., vm, rm, vl, policy). ----
3498 // Check the rounding mode pseudo nodes under RISCVInstrInfoVPseudos.td ----
3499 if (HasRoundingMode) 0
3500 Ops.push_back(True->getOperand(TrueVLIndex - 1)); 0
3501 ----
3502 Ops.append({VL, SEW, PolicyOp}); 0
3503 ----
3504 // Result node should have chain operand of True. ----
3505 if (HasChainOp) 0
3506 Ops.push_back(True.getOperand(TrueChainOpIdx)); 0
3507 ----
3508 // Add the glue for the CopyToReg of mask->v0. ----
3509 Ops.push_back(Glue); 0
3510 ----
3511 SDNode *Result = ----
3512 CurDAG->getMachineNode(MaskedOpc, DL, True->getVTList(), Ops); 0
3513 Result->setFlags(True->getFlags()); 0
3514 ----
3515 // Replace vmerge.vvm node by Result. ----
3516 ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, 0), SDValue(Result, 0)); 0
3517 ----
3518 // Replace another value of True. E.g. chain and VL. ----
3519 for (unsigned Idx = 1; Idx < True->getNumValues(); ++Idx) 0
3520 ReplaceUses(True.getValue(Idx), SDValue(Result, Idx)); 0
3521 ----
3522 // Try to transform Result to unmasked intrinsic. ----
3523 doPeepholeMaskedRVV(Result); 0
3524 return true; 0
3525 } 0
3526 ----
3527 // Transform (VMERGE_VVM_ false, false, true, allones, vl, sew) to ----
3528 // (VMV_V_V_ false, true, vl, sew). It may decrease uses of VMSET. ----
3529 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::performVMergeToVMv(SDNode *N) { 0
3530 #define CASE_VMERGE_TO_VMV(lmul) \ ----
3531 case RISCV::PseudoVMERGE_VVM_##lmul: \ ----
3532 NewOpc = RISCV::PseudoVMV_V_V_##lmul; \ ----
3533 break; ----
3534 unsigned NewOpc; ----
3535 switch (N->getMachineOpcode()) { 0
3536 default: 0
3537 llvm_unreachable("Expected VMERGE_VVM_ instruction."); 0
3538 CASE_VMERGE_TO_VMV(MF8) 0
3539 CASE_VMERGE_TO_VMV(MF4) 0
3540 CASE_VMERGE_TO_VMV(MF2) 0
3541 CASE_VMERGE_TO_VMV(M1) 0
3542 CASE_VMERGE_TO_VMV(M2) 0
3543 CASE_VMERGE_TO_VMV(M4) 0
3544 CASE_VMERGE_TO_VMV(M8) 0
3545 } ----
3546 ----
3547 if (!usesAllOnesMask(N, /* MaskOpIdx */ 3)) 0
3548 return false; 0
3549 ----
3550 SDLoc DL(N); 0
3551 SDValue PolicyOp = ----
3552 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(/*TUMU*/ 0, DL, Subtarget->getXLenVT()); 0
3553 SDNode *Result = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
3554 NewOpc, DL, N->getValueType(0), ----
3555 {N->getOperand(1), N->getOperand(2), N->getOperand(4), N->getOperand(5), 0
3556 PolicyOp}); ----
3557 ReplaceUses(N, Result); 0
3558 return true; 0
3559 } ----
3560 ----
3561 bool RISCVDAGToDAGISel::doPeepholeMergeVVMFold() { 0
3562 bool MadeChange = false; 0
3563 SelectionDAG::allnodes_iterator Position = CurDAG->allnodes_end(); 0
3564 ----
3565 while (Position != CurDAG->allnodes_begin()) { 0
3566 SDNode *N = &*--Position; 0
3567 if (N->use_empty() || !N->isMachineOpcode()) 0
3568 continue; 0
3569 ----
3570 if (IsVMerge(N) || IsVMv(N)) 0
3571 MadeChange |= performCombineVMergeAndVOps(N); 0
3572 if (IsVMerge(N) && N->getOperand(0) == N->getOperand(1)) 0
3573 MadeChange |= performVMergeToVMv(N); 0
3574 } ----
3575 return MadeChange; 0
3576 } ----
3577 ----
3578 // This pass converts a legalized DAG into a RISCV-specific DAG, ready ----
3579 // for instruction scheduling. ----
3580 FunctionPass *llvm::createRISCVISelDag(RISCVTargetMachine &TM, 0
